"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724245","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring a positive outcome for the UK life sciences and pharmaceuticals sector as we exit the European Union.</p><p>In the negotiations, the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States how best to continue to cooperate in the field of medicines regulation in the best interests of both the UK and EU. It would not be appropriate to pre-judge the outcome of the negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","71886 ; 71899","2017-04-27T08:39:39.29Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724245/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724245/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724245/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-25","Drugs: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what the Government's objectives are for regulation for pharmaceuticals after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","71898"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724246","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring a positive outcome for the UK life sciences and pharmaceuticals sector as we exit the European Union.</p><p>In the negotiations, the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States how best to continue to cooperate in the field of medicines regulation in the best interests of both the UK and EU. It would not be appropriate to pre-judge the outcome of the negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","71886 ; 71898","2017-04-27T08:39:39.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724246/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724246/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724246/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-25","European Medicines Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions he has had with EU counterparts on whether the UK will pay the costs of transferring the European Medicines Agency elsewhere in the event of its headquarters leaving London.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","71899"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724247","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government is committed to ensuring a positive outcome for the UK life sciences and pharmaceuticals sector as we exit the European Union.</p><p>In the negotiations, the Government will discuss with the EU and Member States how best to continue to cooperate in the field of medicines regulation in the best interests of both the UK and EU. It would not be appropriate to pre-judge the outcome of the negotiations.</p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker","71898 ; 71899","2017-04-27T08:39:39.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724247/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724247/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724247/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-25","Drugs: Manufacturing Industries","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment he has made of the potential effect on the UK pharmaceutical industry of the UK no longer being part of the European Medicines Agency after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","71886"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724438","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>The UK is supporting the Government of Jordan to deliver the commitment made at the February 2016 Supporting Syria and the Region Conference in London to enable every refugee and vulnerable host community child to access quality education. We are providing up to £80 million over 4 years to support access to education for Syrian refugee children as well as improving the quality of education for all children in Jordan.</p><p>Our support has also contributed to 98 new double shift schools opening this school year. There are now enough spaces for all Syrian and Jordanian children to participate in formal schooling in Jordan.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2017-04-26T16:52:38.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724438/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724438/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724438/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-25","Syria: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what action is being taken to provide education for the children of Syrian refugees in Jordan.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL6829"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724439","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>Currently teaching is a “restricted sector” in Jordan, not open to nationalities other than Jordanian. However, of the approximately 49,000 work permits issued to Syrian refugees to date, 103 Syrians have been employed in the education sector.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2017-04-26T16:46:15.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724439/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724439/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724439/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-25","Syria: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether arrangements are being made for the employment of qualified Syrian teachers who are based in camps or cities in Jordan.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL6830"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724440","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The family reunion policy allows those with refugee status or humanitarian protection to sponsor their partner and children under 18 to join them in the UK, if they formed part of their family unit before the sponsor fled their country.</p><p> </p><p>Those granted refugee status or humanitarian protection are advised about their entitlement to family reunion when they receive their status. There is information on Gov.UK for those wishing to sponsor family members to come to the UK: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/join-family-in-uk/overview" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/join-family-in-uk/overview</a>.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-04-27T13:31:58.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724440/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724440/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724440/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-25","Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they will (1) permit, and (2) encourage, persons resident in the UK to sponsor close relations with refugee status to enter the UK for family reunion.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL6831"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724441","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>DFID is a leading supporter of the Government of Lebanon’s Reaching All Children with Education (RACE II) plan to get all children into education, including by providing £86.6 million via the World Bank to improve access to quality education in Lebanon. Good progress has been made so with almost 300,000 Syrian refugee children now receiving an education.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2017-04-26T16:45:47.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724441/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724441/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724441/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-25","Lebanon: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what progress there has been in increasing the levels of educational attainment or education services in Lebanon, following the agreement in 2016 of a loan by the World Bank for the funding of refugee schooling.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL6832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724442","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>There are currently 928 workers at the King Hussain Development Zone in Mafraq. Of these 835 are Jordanians and 25 are Syrians, with the remaining workers being from other nationalities. Since January 1st 2016, 49,542 work permits have been issued to Syrian refugees in Jordan.</p>",,"Lord Bates",,"2017-04-26T16:47:05.38Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724442/answer","Biography information for Lord Bates","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724442/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724442/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-25","Syria: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many (1) Jordanians, and (2) Syrians, are employed in the King Hussein Development Zone in Jordan, following the agreement with the World Bank, the EU and others.","false","Biography information for Lord Hylton",,"Lord Hylton","HL6833"
