"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724464","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>Information on the number of people with refugee status who were awarded a university place via the UCAS system or who are enrolled at UK universities is not held by the department.</p><p>Student support is available to those recognised as refugees (and their spouses, civil partners and children named on the initial application for asylum), provided they have been ordinarily resident in the British Islands since being recognised by the Government as a refugee and are ordinarily resident in England on the first day of the first academic year of the course. They are exempt from the three year residence requirement.</p><p>Asylum seekers who are recognised as refugees after the start of their course may qualify for support for the remainder of their studies as follows:</p><ul><li>living cost support in any subsequent years of the course (and in the quarters following the award in the year of the award); and</li><li>fee assistance in any subsequent years of the course (and in the year of the award if the award is made within three months of the first day of the academic year of the course).</li></ul><p>Management information from the SLC showing the number of refugee applicants awarded loans in England in each of the last six years can be found in the table below:</p><p><em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p><strong><em>English Domiciled applicants with a refugee status awarded student loans </em></strong></p><p><em>Academic years 2010/11 to 2015/16 (data effective as at the end of each academic year)</em></p><p><em> </em></p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong><em>Academic Year</em></strong></p></td><td><p><strong><em>Number of refugees awarded loans</em></strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2010/11</em></p></td><td><p><em>2,500</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2011/12</em></p></td><td><p><em>3,000</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2012/13</em></p></td><td><p><em>3,700</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2013/14</em></p></td><td><p><em>3,800</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2014/15</em></p></td><td><p><em>3,900</em></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><em>2015/16</em></p></td><td><p><em>3,700</em></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em> </em></p><p><em> </em></p><p><em>Source: SLC, Management Information</em></p><p><em>Note: Awards do not necessarily translate into payments. An awarded applicant will only receive payments once SLC has received confirmation from the student’s provider at the start of the academic year that the student has been registered on the course.</em></p><p><em> </em></p>",,"Viscount Younger of Leckie",,"2017-04-27T14:32:23.69Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724464/answer","Biography information for Viscount Younger of Leckie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724464/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/724464/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-25","Universities: Refugees","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many university places were awarded to people with refugee status in the UK in each year between 2010 and 2016.","false","Biography information for Lord Fink",,"Lord Fink","HL6855"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723708","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>​Our staff in Khartoum and London worked relentlessly to make sure Mr Cox's welfare was protected and his case was handled quickly and fairly. Foreign and Commonwealth Office Ministers raised his case at senior levels in the Sudanese government. The UK takes all allegations of mistreatment of British Nationals very seriously and expresses its deep concern at the allegations raised by Mr Cox. The British Embassy in Khartoum raised our concerns about the allegations with the Government of Sudan and have requested that a thorough, independent and impartial investigation is undertaken. On the treatment of Mr Daoud Hari, as he is not a British National, it is not within our consular remit to raise allegations of his mistreatment with the Government of Sudan.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2017-04-27T12:10:55.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723708/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723708/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723708/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Sudan: Press Freedom","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what representations they have made to the government of Sudan regarding the abduction and torture of the journalist Phil Cox and the translator Daoud Hari; and, whether they intend to raise the treatment of those two individuals with the EU and the UN Human Rights Council.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL6751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723709","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The OPCW asked the Government of Sudan, as a State Party to the Chemical Weapons Convention, to share all relevant information, and offered its assistance in any investigation. The Sudanese authorities have since reported to the OPCW that their national investigations have found no evidence of chemical weapon use in the Jebel Marra region. Separately, we continue to press the Government of Sudan, most recently at the UK-Sudan Strategic Dialogue on 29 March, to allow the AU/UN Peacekeeping Mission in Darfur (UNAMID) unrestricted access to all parts of Darfur.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2017-04-27T12:19:56.253Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723709/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723709/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723709/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Darfur: Chemical Weapons","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what plans they have to establish whether chemical weapons have been used against the civilian population in Darfur.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL6752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723711","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The UK Government welcomes any efforts to counter extremist ideology, including those of Egypt's Dar al-Ifta, and is strongly supportive of the Egyptian Government's commitment to protect the rights of minorities and promote religious tolerance.</p><p>The UK has also been working with al-Azhar university in Egypt for ten years. The aim of this work is to help develop a new generation of religious leaders who are equipped to build dialogue across different cultures and religions, and confront extremism. The work includes English teaching, debating skills training, and a postgraduate scholarship scheme.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2017-04-27T12:36:53.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723711/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723711/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723711/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Egypt: Christianity","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of reports that Egypt's Grand Mufti, Shawki Allam, has identified 3,000 fatwas inciting the destruction of churches in Egypt; and, what support they are providing to the Grand Mufti and the government of Egypt to identify and combat sources of extremism.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL6753"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723712","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>These cases have been investigated in the Republic of Korea (ROK) by the relevant ROK authorities. It is for the ROK authorities to determine if these cases involve terrorist acts, in line with the relevant legal framework.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2017-04-27T12:00:59.9Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723712/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723712/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723712/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","North Korea: Terrorism","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Anelay of St Johns on 5 April (HL6328), what discussions they have had with the investigating authorities to determine whether the DPRK's actions constitute an act of terrorism under the UK's domestic legal definition.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL6754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723713","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>​The UK has complied with all provisions of the EU designation of Korea National Insurance Company (KNIC). The decision to sanction individuals or entities is taken on a case by case basis in line with evidence. The EU designated the London office of the KNIC on 28 April 2016 and since then the UK has taken the appropriate actions to sanction the firm.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2017-04-27T12:02:37.393Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723713/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723713/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723713/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Korea National Insurance Corporation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Baroness Anelay of St Johns on 3 February (HL4923), whether they have anything to add to their reply about the activities of the Korea National Insurance Corporation; whether they believe that the activities of that Corporation are licit and lawful and whether they believe funds generated by the Corporation have aided the government of North Korea in the development of its nuclear weapons programme.","false","Biography information for Lord Alton of Liverpool",,"Lord Alton of Liverpool","HL6755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723714","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-26","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to this question in the time available before Prorogation. Ministers will correspond directly with the Member.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2017-04-26T11:17:29.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723714/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723714/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723714/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-24","Non-domestic Rates","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the letter from Lord Young of Cookham to Lord Beecham on 5 April regarding the Non-Domestic Rating (Rates Retention) and (Levy and Safety Net) (Amendment) Regulations 2017, a copy of which has been placed in the Library of the House, (1) how many challenges to the 2010 rating lists are outstanding for each year since 2010, (2) how long they estimate it will take to determine those challenges, and (3) what is their estimate of the financial impact of successful challenges on local authorities.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL6756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723715","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-27","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to this question in the time available before Prorogation. The Minister will correspond directly with the Peer.</p>",,"Lord Keen of Elie","HL6758","2017-04-27T16:14:34.757Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723715/answer","Biography information for Lord Keen of Elie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723715/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723715/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-24","Winchester Prison","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether the number of staff at HMP Winchester adequately trained in suicide and self-harm prevention has only increased from 41 per cent to 61 per cent since July 2015; and if so why.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL6757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723716","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-27","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to this question in the time available before Prorogation. The Minister will correspond directly with the Peer.</p>",,"Lord Keen of Elie","HL6757","2017-04-27T16:14:34.693Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723716/answer","Biography information for Lord Keen of Elie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723716/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723716/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-24","Winchester Prison","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they expect all staff at HMP Winchester to be adequately trained in suicide and self-harm prevention.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL6758"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723717","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-27","<p>All staff in contact with prisoners are required to receive training on suicide and self-harm prevention.</p><p> </p><p>We have also developed a new ‘Introduction to Suicide and Self-Harm Prevention’ course that includes a module on mental health awareness. From May 2017 this will be provided as part of the entry level training for new prison officers, and nearly three hundred trainers have been trained to facilitate its delivery in prisons as refresher training for existing staff.</p><p> </p><p>We do not hold centrally the amount spent in all prisons on suicide and self-harm prevention training.</p>",,"Lord Keen of Elie","HL6760","2017-04-27T15:08:53.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723717/answer","Biography information for Lord Keen of Elie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723717/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723717/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-24","Prisoners: Suicide","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their estimate of the proportion of staff in all custodial institutions who are adequately trained in suicide and self-harm prevention.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL6759"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723718","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-04-27","<p>All staff in contact with prisoners are required to receive training on suicide and self-harm prevention.</p><p> </p><p>We have also developed a new ‘Introduction to Suicide and Self-Harm Prevention’ course that includes a module on mental health awareness. From May 2017 this will be provided as part of the entry level training for new prison officers, and nearly three hundred trainers have been trained to facilitate its delivery in prisons as refresher training for existing staff.</p><p> </p><p>We do not hold centrally the amount spent in all prisons on suicide and self-harm prevention training.</p>",,"Lord Keen of Elie","HL6759","2017-04-27T15:08:53.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723718/answer","Biography information for Lord Keen of Elie","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723718/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723718/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-04-24","Prisoners: Suicide","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is the estimated annual expenditure on suicide and self-harm prevention training across the custodial system (1) in gross terms, and (2) per capita, in relation to (a) officers, and (b) prisoners.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL6760"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723719","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Home Office is committed to protecting the rights of all asylum seekers and providing those who are destitute with safe, secure accommodation. There is a rigorous contract compliance regime in place to ensure that the required performance standards are met; this includes regular inspections. Clearsprings Ready Homes is required to inspect all of their properties each month and the Home Office inspects over a third of the property portfolio each year. Where property does not meet the required standards there are strict time limits on resolving the defects; failure to meet those time limits can result in service credits being applied.</p><p>Clearsprings Ready Homes deliver services in London and the South of England Region and Wales. The Home Office publishes quarterly figures on the number of asylum seekers housed in dispersed accommodation, including under Section 95, by region in the Immigration Statistics release, in table as_16q and 17q in volume 4 of the Asylum data tables. These are available at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-july-to-september-2016/list-of-tables#asylum" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/immigration-statistics-july-to-september-2016/list-of-tables#asylum</a></p><p> </p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-04-27T11:54:20.417Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723719/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723719/answer","16q and 17q in Vol 4 - Asylum Data Tables.xlsx","16q and 17q in Vol 4 - Asylum Data Tables.xlsx","16q and 17q - Vol 4 - Asylum Data Tables ","16q and 17q - Vol 4 - Asylum Data Tables ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723719/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","ClearSprings Group","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what steps they are taking to assess the condition of premises provided by Clearsprings Ready Homes Ltd to accommodate refugees and asylum seekers; and how many asylum seekers are currently housed by Clearsprings Ready Homes Ltd.","false","Biography information for Lord Beecham",,"Lord Beecham","HL6761"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723720","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government has made no assessment of the effect of leaving the EU on the UK’s GDP per hour worked compared to that of other countries.</p>",,"Baroness Neville-Rolfe",,"2017-04-27T10:53:04.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723720/answer","Biography information for Baroness Neville-Rolfe","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723720/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723720/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-24","Productivity","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the effect of Brexit on the UK's GDP per hour worked, in comparison to (1) Germany, (2) France, and (3) Italy.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL6762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723721","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Competition and Markets Authority (CMA) makes independent decisions on what to investigate. If there is information suggesting that anti-competitive collusion or abuse of dominant position might have occurred, it can be shared with the CMA. The CMA will consider whether there are matters that should be investigated under its enforcement powers.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2017-04-27T13:55:33.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723721/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723721/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723721/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-24","Garden Bridge","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether they intend to ask the Competition and Markets Authority to investigate whether the procurement processes described in Dame Margaret Hodge's review of the proposed London Garden Bridge, published on 7 April, comply with best practice for government-funded projects.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL6763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723722","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-26","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to this question in the time available before Prorogation. Ministers will correspond directly with the Member.</p>",,"Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth",,"2017-04-26T11:17:42.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723722/answer","Biography information for Lord Bourne of Aberystwyth","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723722/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723722/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-24","Government Departments: Land","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government whether operational government land can be disposed of on a freehold basis.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL6764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723723","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-26","<p>As recommended by the 2015 Hendy Review, Network Rail is committed to disposing of assets, including freight estate, where ownership is not essential for the running of the railway. As well as generating funds to reinvest into the railway, this will allow Network Rail to focus on its core business of running a safe, reliable and growing network.</p><p> </p><p>At this point in time all options are still being considered and no firm decisions have been made about freight asset sales. The detail of any expected future asset sales is commercially sensitive.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2017-04-26T10:58:20.43Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723723/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723723/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723723/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-24","Network Rail: Land","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what is their estimate of the expected income from Network Rail’s disposal of operational freight land.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL6765"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723724","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-26","<p>Spending Review 2015 set a long term funding envelope for HS2 of £55.7 billion in 2015 prices, which remains unchanged.</p><p> </p><p>The key funding assumption remains that HS2 will be fully publicly funded upfront. The Department for Transport and HS2 Limited will investigate private financing and third party funding, where this could reduce cost to the taxpayer and promote value for money.</p><p> </p><p>In relation to Manchester Airport station, the funding arrangements are yet to be concluded but the Government has made clear that development of a station at Manchester Airport is dependent on agreeing an appropriate local funding package. HS2 Ltd’s budgeting is in line with that and HS2 Ltd will continue to pursue avenues that encourage third party, non-Governmental funding.</p>",,"Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon",,"2017-04-26T10:59:08.057Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723724/answer","Biography information for Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723724/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723724/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-24","High Speed 2 Railway Line","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, further to the Written Answer by Lord Ahmad of Wimbledon on 21 December 2016 (HL4189), whether the funding envelope for HS2 set by the Spending Review 2015 is unchanged; and what allowance, if any, they expect to be added to those figures in respect of developer contributions to station construction; and what, if any, government guarantees will be assumed for such private sector contributions.","false","Biography information for Lord Berkeley",,"Lord Berkeley","HL6766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723725","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>We provided Andrew Hall with the appropriate levels of consular assistance at the time of his arrest and during his trial in Thailand.</p>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2017-04-27T12:25:18.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723725/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723725/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723725/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Andy Hall","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assistance they are providing to the British human rights activist Andy Hall who was convicted of defamation and computer crimes in Thailand in September 2016.","false","Biography information for Baroness Goudie",,"Baroness Goudie","HL6767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723726","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>Regulation of the private security industry was included within the scope of the recent review of the Security Industry Authority, which sought evidence from the industry. The Government’s response to the review may include measures requiring a review of regulations issued.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-04-27T12:07:51.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723726/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723726/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723726/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Security Guards: Regulation","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government when they next intend to review the regulations issued under the Private Security Industry Act 2002; and what representations they have received about those regulations from (1) the Security Industry Authority, (2) bodies representing security companies, including those representing the smaller security companies, and (3) bodies representing security officers.","false","Biography information for Lord Harris of Haringey",,"Lord Harris of Haringey","HL6768"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723727","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Security Industry Authority operates a voluntary Approved Contractor Scheme which measures private security suppliers against independently assessed criteria. There are 831 companies currently registered under this scheme.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-04-26T16:10:02.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723727/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723727/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723727/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Security Guards: Licensing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what proportion of security companies are members of the SIA Approved Contractor Scheme; and what measures they are taking to encourage security companies to join the Approved Contractor Scheme.","false","Biography information for Lord Harris of Haringey",,"Lord Harris of Haringey","HL6769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723728","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-04-26T16:10:57.713Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723728/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723728/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723728/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Security Guards: Licensing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what proportion of security contracts let by (1) central government departments, (2) government agencies, (3) NHS bodies, and (4) local government, are to members of the SIA Approved Contractor Scheme.","false","Biography information for Lord Harris of Haringey",,"Lord Harris of Haringey","HL6770"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723729","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government cannot comment on individual cases. The Government has not made any assessment of the use of zero-hour or self-employment contracts in the security industry.</p><p>The availability of atypical or non-standard forms of employment provide a number of benefits for workers who cannot or do not want to commit to ‘standard’ full-time employment. This Government is absolutely clear that employers must take their employment law responsibilities seriously and cannot simply opt out of their responsibilities. We believe everyone deserves to be treated fairly at work.</p>",,"Lord Prior of Brampton",,"2017-04-27T13:56:16.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723729/answer","Biography information for Lord Prior of Brampton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723729/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723729/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-24","Security Guards: Conditions of Employment","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of the recent ruling in respect of the employment status of Uber drivers on the security industry; and what is their assessment of the use of zero-hour or self-employment contracts in the security industry.","false","Biography information for Lord Harris of Haringey",,"Lord Harris of Haringey","HL6771"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723730","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>No assessment has been made of the potential benefit for the rest of the UK of the work done by the Scottish Procurement Directorate in relation to the Approved Contractor Scheme.</p>",,"Baroness Williams of Trafford",,"2017-04-26T16:10:45.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723730/answer","Biography information for Baroness Williams of Trafford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723730/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723730/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Security Guards: Licensing","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what assessment they have made of whether the work done by the Scottish Procurement Directorate to promote the use of the SIA Approved Contractor Scheme in public body contracts for security services in Scotland might be a model that would have a beneficial effect elsewhere in the UK.","false","Biography information for Lord Harris of Haringey",,"Lord Harris of Haringey","HL6772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723731","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>Work on a virtual National Security Academy has begun, with departments agreeing to take a shared approach and cross-community training being developed in specific areas. It has held its first course on Full Spectrum Effects. Open to staff across government, the FCO Diplomatic Academy has launched a Security, Defence and Intelligence faculty, which will further develop knowledge and skills on international security.</p>",,"Lord Young of Cookham",,"2017-04-26T16:43:36.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723731/answer","Biography information for Lord Young of Cookham","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723731/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-04-24","National Security: Training","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government what progress has been made towards creating the virtual National Security Academy announced in the 2015 National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review.","false","Biography information for Lord Hennessy of Nympsfield",,"Lord Hennessy of Nympsfield","HL6773"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723732","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The 2016/2017 UN Handbook shows that there is one UK citizen on each of the following seven UN and UN agency committees:</p><ul><li>Committee on Contributions;</li><li>International Law Commission;</li><li>UN Mechanism for International Criminal Tribunals;</li><li>Committee of Experts on International Cooperation in Tax Matters;</li><li>International Court of Justice;</li><li>Sub Committee on the Prevention of Torture (sub-committee of the Committee Against Torture);</li><li>Commission on the Limits of the Continental Shelf.</li></ul>",,"Baroness Anelay of St Johns",,"2017-04-27T12:26:43.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723732/answer","Biography information for Baroness Anelay of St Johns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723732/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723732/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","United Nations: Public Appointments","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government how many appointments, other than as employees, to UN committees and agencies are held by representatives or citizens nominated by the UK; and what are those positions.","false","Biography information for Baroness Hodgson of Abinger",,"Baroness Hodgson of Abinger","HL6774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723733","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","true","2017-04-27","<p><del class="ministerial"><em>It has not proved possible to respond to this question in the time available before Prorogation. Ministers will correspond directly with the Member.</em></del></p><p><ins class="ministerial">Pesticides can only be sold and used if they are authorised. Authorisation is only granted if scientific data demonstrate that the proposed use of the pesticide will not have any harmful effects on human health or any unacceptable effect on the environment. The assessment of risks to human health takes account of the potential for exposure of rural residents.</ins></p><p> </p>",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble",,"2017-04-27T10:57:38.943Z","2017-04-27T15:07:17.177Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723733/answer","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723733/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723733/answer",,"Lord Gardiner of Kimble","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723733/answer/previousversion/46574","Biography information for Lord Gardiner of Kimble","13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-24","Pesticides","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty’s Government, in the light of the recommendations of the March 2017 report of the UN Special Rapporteur on the Right to Food on pesticide use in agriculture, what steps they are taking to protect rural residents and communities from the detrimental health impact of pesticides.","false","Biography information for Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb",,"Baroness Jones of Moulsecoomb","HL6775"
