"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723826","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-27","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave on 22 November 2016 to Question 53647 to the hon. Member for Blaenau Gwent (Mr Smith).</p>","Sevenoaks","Sir Michael Fallon",,"2017-04-27T08:04:05.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723826/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723826/answer","Hansard Extract 17 November 2017 53647.docx","Hansard Extract 17 November 2017 53647.docx","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","Joint Strike Fighter Aircraft","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723826/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-24","Ministry of Defence: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the baseline increase attributable to currency fluctuations in his Department's budget (a) is for the current and (b) was for previous financial year.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","71827"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723827","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Northern Ireland Assembly agreed to nominate appropriate representatives to the national governance bodies of the Armed Forces Covenant on 6 December 2016. The Secretary of State for Northern Ireland has urged all parties to make appropriate nominations to the Covenant's national governance bodies a priority for the devolved Government once reconvened. In the interim, Northern Ireland's interests on the national governance bodies of the Armed Forces Covenant are represented by Ministers and officials from the Northern Ireland Office.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2017-04-27T08:05:00.22Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723827/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723827/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723827/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-24","Armed Forces Covenant Reference Group: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what effect the absence of a functioning Northern Ireland Executive has on the ability of the recent appointment of the Northern Ireland representative to the UK-wide Covenant Reference Group to carry out her role.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","71785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723828","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>​The Counter Proliferation and Arms Control Centre is funded by the contributing departments through their own budgets. The Ministry of Defence provides the office space, with each department funding its own staff and IT systems. There is no specific operating budget.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-26T14:35:59.17Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723828/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723828/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Counter Proliferation and Arms Control Centre","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what the total operating budget of the Counter Proliferation and Arms Control Centre was in the most recent year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71783"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723829","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-27","<p>Russian maritime operations are closely monitored. According to Russian doctrine, the purpose of Russian naval activity is to conduct routine operations in support of their national interests, which Russia sees as including surveillance of UK and NATO maritime operations. The general trend of Russian naval activity has been to increase, year on year, since a post-cold war low point around 2000. Russia has a long standing policy of using its maritime capabilities to send strategic messages.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-04-27T08:15:53.86Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723829/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723829/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-24","Russia: Navy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of (a) the purpose and (b) trends in the level of Russian naval activity around the Greenland-Iceland-UK gap; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","71786"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723830","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-27","<p>The answer can be found on page 148 of the Ministry of Defence's 2015-16 Annual Report and Accounts which is available at the following link:</p><p>https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/558559/MoD_AR16.pdf</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-27T08:16:27.583Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723830/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723830/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-24","Ministry of Defence: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the value of forward purchase contracts with the Bank of England for the financial years (a) 2016-17 and (b) 2017-18 is; and what proportion of his Department's expenditure in each of those years those figures represent.","false","Biography information for Jenny Chapman","Darlington","Jenny Chapman","71791"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723831","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-27","<p>The order of battle and current locations of units in 12<sup>th</sup> (Armoured Infantry) Brigade is set out below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Unit</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Location</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HQ 12<sup>th</sup> (Armoured Infantry) Brigade</p></td><td><p>Bulford Garrison</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>The Kings Royal Hussars</p></td><td><p>Tidworth Garrison</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>The Royal Lancers (Queen Elizabeth’s Own)</p></td><td><p>Catterick Garrison</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1<sup>st</sup> Battalion Scots Guards</p></td><td><p>Aldershot Garrison</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1<sup>st</sup> Battalion The Yorkshire Regiment</p></td><td><p>Tidworth Garrison</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>1<sup>St</sup> Battalion The Royal Welsh</p></td><td><p>Tidworth Garrison</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>The Royal Wessex Yeomanry, an Army Reserve Regiment based across Dorset, Devon and Wiltshire also provides support to 12<sup>th </sup>(Armoured Infantry) Brigade.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2017-04-27T08:14:08.643Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723831/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723831/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-24","Army","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what the Order of Battle is and basing arrangements are for 12th Mechanized Brigade.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","71816"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723832","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The UK-Gulf Co-operation Council Strategic Partnership covers a broad range of areas of cooperation, including addressing regional foreign policy challenges, counter-terrorism and border security, cyber security, human trafficking, and improving trade and investment ties. Productive discussions have continued since December 2016, and delivery and implementation are ongoing.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-04-27T08:35:41.327Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723832/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723832/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723832/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Gulf Cooperation Council","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what progress his Department has made on the new Strategic Partnership between the UK and the Gulf Co-operation Council announced in December 2016; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","71806"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723833","Ministry of Defence","false","2017-04-27","<p>Forward contracts are placed to cover a proportion of forecast expenditure in US Dollars and Euros. The department keeps detailed records of the forward purchase contracts placed, which cannot be released as its disclosure would prejudice commercial interests.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2017-04-27T08:10:30.277Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723833/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723833/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723833/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2017-04-24","Ministry of Defence: Public Expenditure","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, whether his Department keeps copies of planning documents for forward purchase contracts with the Bank of England.","false","Biography information for Douglas Chapman","Dunfermline and West Fife","Douglas Chapman","71828"
