"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723837","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>The numbers of three- and four-year-olds accessing funded early years education, by local authority, is available on the Department’s website at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/education-provision-children-under-5-years-of-age-january-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/education-provision-children-under-5-years-of-age-january-2016</a></p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-04-27T07:23:04.533Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723837/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723837/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723837/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-24","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of families in Southampton, Itchen constituency make use of the 15-hours a week of free childcare for three and four-year olds.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","71818"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723838","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>The requested information is not collected centrally.</p><p>High needs funding supports provision for pupils and students with special educational needs and disabilities (SEND) from their early years to 25. Local authorities should use their high needs budget to provide the most appropriate support package for an individual with SEN in a range of settings. It is also intended to support good quality alternative provision for pupils who cannot receive their education in schools for medical or other reasons.</p><p>Local authorities also use their high needs budget to pay for central services relating to SEND and alternative provision, as permitted by <a href="http://www.legislation.gov.uk/uksi/2017/44/contents/made" target="_blank">The School and Early Years Finance (England) Regulations 2017</a>.</p><p>The number of pupils for whom schools receive high needs funding from their local authority has been published as part of the import/export adjustment in the <a href="https://consult.education.gov.uk/funding-policy-unit/high-needs-funding-reform-2/supporting_documents/Illustrative%20high%20needs%20national%20funding%20formula%20allocations.xlsm" target="_blank">illustrative high needs allocations</a> from the second stage consultation on high needs funding reform.</p><p>The number of children with statements of SEN and education, health and care (EHC) plans in each local authority area has been published as <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/statements-of-sen-and-ehc-plans-england-2016" target="_blank">national statistics</a>.</p><p>Information from the schools census on pupils with SEN and SEN provision in schools has been published in <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/special-educational-needs-in-england-january-2016" target="_blank">Statistical First Release: Special Educational Needs in England</a>. This includes underlying data at individual school level.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-04-27T07:24:41.56Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723838/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723838/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723838/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-24","Special Educational Needs: Southampton Itchen","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of pupils in Southampton, Itchen constituency are in receipt of high needs block education funding.","false","Biography information for Royston Smith","Southampton, Itchen","Royston Smith","71819"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723839","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2017-04-27T08:54:03.227Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723839/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723839/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723839/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-24","Johnson Kane","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what background checks were carried out on Johnson Kane, the co-founder and chief executive officer of the Education Fellowship Trust, in advance of schools being transferred to that multi-academy trust.","false","Biography information for Mr Barry Sheerman","Huddersfield","Mr Barry Sheerman","71707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723840","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Department publishes both pupil level projections and, separately, data on the numbers in school on an annual basis. The most recent figures on the numbers in school are from January 2016 school census and can be found in the statistical first release available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2016" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/schools-pupils-and-their-characteristics-january-2016</a>.</p><p>The 2015 projection of the 2016 school population (published at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/national-pupil-projections-trends-in-pupil-numbers-july-2015" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/national-pupil-projections-trends-in-pupil-numbers-july-2015</a>), and the equivalent school census figures, are given in the table below.</p><p> </p><p><strong>Projected and actual school population, January 2016, England</strong></p><p>Full-time equivalent figures up to and including age 15</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>All schools<sup>1</sup></p></td><td><p>State funded schools<sup>2</sup></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016 census</p></td><td><p>7,842</p></td><td><p>7,365</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015 projection for 2016</p></td><td><p>7,837</p></td><td><p>7,362</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em> thousands</em></p><p>1 State funded nursery, primary, secondary, special and alternative provisions schools, plus independent and non-maintained special schools</p><p>2 As 1 but omitting independent and non-maintained special schools</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-04-27T07:28:57.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723840/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723840/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723840/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-24","Pupil Numbers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the difference is between the number of pupils currently studying in England and the number forecasted in 2015.","false","Biography information for Charlotte Leslie","Bristol North West","Charlotte Leslie","71754"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723841","Department for Education","false","2017-04-27","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2017-04-27T11:09:00.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723841/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723841/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723841/answer",,,,,"60","Education","Education","2017-04-24","Schools: Admissions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what progress the Government has made in strengthening the (a) rights of parents of summer born-children to defer the year of their child's entry to school and (b) right for a child to remain in the same academic year irrespective of changes in school or local authority; and when the Government plans to consult on proposed changes to the Admissions Code.","false","Biography information for Helen Hayes","Dulwich and West Norwood","Helen Hayes","71672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723842","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-27","<p /><p> </p><p>The Government set out its position on this and other recommendations in its response, which was published in February, to the review by the Parliamentary Select Committee on Environment, Food &amp; Rural Affairs, entitled <em>Animal Welfare in England: Domestic Pets. </em></p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-27T06:57:26.943Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723842/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723842/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723842/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-24","Dogs: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if the Government will take steps to ensure that puppies are not sold without their mothers being present.","false","Biography information for Alex Salmond","Gordon","Alex Salmond","71673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723843","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>It is estimated that 1% of the population is affected by coeliac disease. No estimate has been made of effects on people in the manufacturing industry if supply on prescription changes. The impact assessment measures health impacts of all three options that are contained in the published Gluten Free consultation. The impact assessment will be developed further once the consultation responses have been analysed. More information can be found by following this link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/availability-of-gluten-free-foods-on-nhs-prescription" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/availability-of-gluten-free-foods-on-nhs-prescription</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T08:45:17.657Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723843/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723843/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723843/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Coeliac Disease: Prescriptions","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what estimate he has made of the number of (a) coeliacs, (b) people working in the manufacturing industry and (c) other people who will be affected by the proposal to remove gluten-free provisions from prescription.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","71681"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723845","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-27","<p>Defra works with local authorities and the Waste and Resources Action Programme (WRAP) to provide advice and promote best practice among local authorities on waste and recycling. Local councils, and householders have played a key role in increasing the UK’s recycling rate from 11% at the turn of the century to 44% in 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p>Greater consistency in local authority recycling – taking account of best practice – in particular has potential to increase recycling rates further. WRAP are working with an Advisory Group of waste stakeholders, to look at the benefits and opportunities from having greater consistency in the materials collected and collection systems to enable local authorities to recycle more, and to make it easier for householders to put the right materials in the right bin.</p><p> </p><p>Recycle Now, launched in 2004, is the national recycling campaign for England. It is supported and funded by Defra and managed by WRAP. It is used locally by over 90% of Local Authorities in England and includes information to inform people about the many items that can be recycled around the home.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","71711","2017-04-27T06:16:42.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723845/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723845/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723845/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-24","Recycling: Publicity","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to improve people's knowledge of the merits of recycling.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","71710"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723846","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-27","<p>Defra works with local authorities and the Waste and Resources Action Programme (WRAP) to provide advice and promote best practice among local authorities on waste and recycling. Local councils, and householders have played a key role in increasing the UK’s recycling rate from 11% at the turn of the century to 44% in 2015/16.</p><p> </p><p>Greater consistency in local authority recycling – taking account of best practice – in particular has potential to increase recycling rates further. WRAP are working with an Advisory Group of waste stakeholders, to look at the benefits and opportunities from having greater consistency in the materials collected and collection systems to enable local authorities to recycle more, and to make it easier for householders to put the right materials in the right bin.</p><p> </p><p>Recycle Now, launched in 2004, is the national recycling campaign for England. It is supported and funded by Defra and managed by WRAP. It is used locally by over 90% of Local Authorities in England and includes information to inform people about the many items that can be recycled around the home.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey","71710","2017-04-27T06:16:42.357Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723846/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723846/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723846/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-24","Recycling: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to spread best practice on recycling.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","71711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723847","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-27","<p /><p>Three neonicotinoids are currently subject to restrictions which normally prohibit their use on a number of crops. Two emergency authorisations have been granted for the use of these restricted neonicotinoids. Those authorisations, issued in July 2015, allowed limited and controlled use on oilseed rape until November 2015. In total, eight applications for use of the same neonicotinoids have been turned down between 2015 and 2017. All decisions are made on the basis of advice from the independent UK Expert Committee on Pesticides.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-27T06:55:54.787Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723847/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723847/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723847/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-24","Neonicotinoids","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, pursuant to the Answer of 24 April 2017 to Question 71069, how many emergency authorisation applications for the use of neonicotinoid pesticides the Government has approved in the last (a) 12 and (b) 24 months.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","71757"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723848","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-26","<p>HM Treasury has responsibility for taxation and the letter has been passed on for the responsible Minister to respond.</p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-04-26T11:59:49.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723848/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723848/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723848/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-24","FairFuelUK","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, whether she has responded to FairFuelUK's letter of 7 April 2017 requesting a meeting on taxation and diesel cars; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Alex Salmond","Gordon","Alex Salmond","71774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723849","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-27","<p><em>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</em></p><p> </p>","Suffolk Coastal","Dr Thérèse Coffey",,"2017-04-27T06:56:28.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723849/answer","Biography information for Dr Thérèse  Coffey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723849/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723849/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-24","Curlews: Conservation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps her Department is taking to (a) protect and retain habitats for the curlew and (b) further assist in fox and crow control to maintain curlew numbers.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","71718"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723850","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-27","<p /><p> </p><p>Glyphosate is important to British farming and there would be real difficulties if it were no longer available. UK and EU experts have identified no safety concerns which would preclude the continuing use of glyphosate.</p><p> </p><p>Defra considers that decisions on the use of pesticides should be based on a careful scientific assessment of the risks, with the aim of achieving a high level of protection for people and the environment.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-27T06:56:50.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723850/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723850/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723850/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-24","Agriculture: Glyphosate","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what steps she is taking to ensure that glyphosate continues to be available for use by farmers after the UK leaves the EU.","false","Biography information for Mr Steve Baker","Wycombe","Steve Baker","71738"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723851","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-04-27","<p /><p>The Government set out its position on these and other recommendations in its response, which was published in February, to the review by the Parliamentary Select Committee on Environment, Food &amp; Rural Affairs, entitled <em>Animal Welfare in England: Domestic Pets. </em></p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-04-27T06:57:08.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723851/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723851/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723851/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-04-24","Dogs: Sales","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, if she will make an assessment of the International Fund for Animal Welfare's proposals of February 2017 to (a) ban sales of puppies through third party intermediaries, (b) ensure all dog purchases are traceable through a robust licensing system and (c) place greater legal restrictions on online puppy sales.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","71815"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723852","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>I have not had recent discussions with my US counterpart on the US's potential designation of Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps (IRGC) as a foreign terrorist organisation.</p><p> </p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-26T13:57:45.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723852/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723852/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723852/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Iranian Revolutionary Guard Corps","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his US counterpart on the potential designation by that country of Iran's Islamic Revolutionary Guard Corps as a foreign terrorist organisation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71799"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723853","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>Consideration of the application of international humanitarian law, the body of law which regulates the conduct of armed conflict, including seeking to limit the effects of conflict on civilians for humanitarian reasons, and international human rights law, the body of law which seeks to protect human rights and fundamental freedoms, is considered more appropriately under Criterion Two of the Consolidated EU &amp; National Arms Export Licensing Criteria, which refers specifically to international human rights instruments and international humanitarian law.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-26T14:22:04.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723853/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723853/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723853/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Arms Trade: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to Criterion Four of the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria, whether his Department's interpretation of an adverse impact on regional peace and security includes any potential effect on the civilian population of a country in whose territory the country of final destination is engaged in armed conflict.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71805"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723854","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>No. Criterion Three of the Consolidated EU &amp; National Arms Export Licensing Criteria refers specifically to “the internal situation in the country of final destination, as a function of the existence of tensions or armed conflicts” and not to external conflicts, which would be considered under other Criteria.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-26T13:44:02.317Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723854/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723854/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723854/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Arms Trade: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to Criterion Three of the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria, whether his Department's interpretation of whether items would provoke or prolong armed conflicts in the country of final destination extends to external conflicts to which the country of final destination is a party.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71729"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723855","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>I am deeply concerned by recent developments relating to the Baha’i community in Yemen. The Houthis and all parties in Yemen must respect freedom of religion and the rights of all Yemenis.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-04-27T08:30:56.99Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723855/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723855/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723855/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Yemen: Baha'i Faith","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports his Department has received of mass arrests of Baha'is in Sana'a, Yemen during April 2017; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","71717"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723856","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The UK is very concerned by the decision of Russia's Supreme Court to categorise the Jehovah's Witnesses as &quot;extremists&quot;. This ruling effectively criminalises the peaceful worship by 175,000 Russian citizens and is at odds with the right to religious freedom enshrined in the Russian Constitution. The Minister of State, The Baroness Anelay of St Johns, issued a statement on 21 April expressing these concerns.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-04-27T11:00:55.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723856/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723856/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723856/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Russia: Jehovah's Witnesses","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what reports he has received on recent restrictions placed on the activities of Jehovah's Witnesses in Russia.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","71716"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723857","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The key issue when considering export licence applications under Criterion Two of the Consolidated EU &amp; National Arms Export Licensing Criteria is whether there is a clear risk that the items to be licensed might be used in the commission of a serious violation of international humanitarian law. It is not necessary, nor always possible, to make a determination about specific past incidents as to whether serious violations of international humanitarian law have occurred.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-27T09:42:30.003Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723857/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723857/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723857/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Arms Trade: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to Criterion Two of the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria, whether his Department's interpretation of a clear risk that items could be used in the commission of serious violations of international humanitarian law establishes a competent authority for determining whether serious violations of international humanitarian law have occurred.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71734"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723858","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>My officials have had ongoing discussions with their United States counterparts about the Muslim Brotherhood. If the United States were to designate the Muslim Brotherhood, we would consider any new evidence carefully against our own evidential thresholds for a UK listing. The Government will ensure that any potential action we take complements our strong collaboration with regional partners on our shared counter terrorism priorities.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-26T14:15:53.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723858/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723858/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723858/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Muslim Brotherhood","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the potential implications of designation by the United States of the Muslim Brotherhood as a foreign terrorist organisation on regional co-operation on counter-terrorism in the Middle East and North Africa.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71733"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723859","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>​It would not be appropriate to speculate about the implications of a potential US designation. The UK remains committed to the implementation of the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPoA). Consistent with Under the JCPoA, the Islamic Revolutionary General Corps (IRGC) remains sanctioned.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-26T13:50:08.763Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723859/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723859/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723859/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Iranian Revolutionary Guard Corps","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the potential implications of designation by the United States of Iran's Islamic Revolutionary General Corps as a foreign terrorist organisation for the implementation of the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action with Iran.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71730"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723860","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>​It would not be appropriate to speculate about the implications of a potential US designation. The UK is working as part of the 68 member Global Coalition, in which we continue to play a leading role, to support the Iraqi Government to clear Daesh from its territory in a way that protects civilians, minimises the humanitarian impact, and limits longer-term conflict by supporting political reconciliation.</p><p> </p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-26T14:03:35.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723860/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723860/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723860/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Iranian Revolutionary Guard Corps","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what assessment he has made of the potential implications of designation by the United States of Iran's Islamic Revolutionary General Corps as a foreign terrorist organisation for co-operation between Iran and Iraq in the campaign against Daesh.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71731"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723861","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>​My officials have had ongoing discussions with their United States counterparts about the Muslim Brotherhood. If the United States were to designate the Muslim Brotherhood, we would consider any new evidence carefully against our own evidential thresholds for a UK listing. The Government will ensure that any potential action we take complements our strong collaboration with regional partners on our shared counter terrorism priorities.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-26T14:04:22.33Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723861/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723861/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723861/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Muslim Brotherhood","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what recent discussions he has had with his counterpart in the United States on the potential designation by that country of the Muslim Brotherhood as a foreign terrorist organisation; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71732"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723862","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>My department has received such notifications on 26 occasions since 26 March 2015. Information on denials is shared between EU Member States on a confidential basis and it is not possible to provide further information on specific refusal notifications.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-27T09:34:00.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723862/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723862/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723862/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Saudi Arabia: Arms Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, on how many occasions since 26 March 2015 his Department's Arms Export Policy Team has received notification of another EU member state's decision to refuse arms export licence applications in which Saudi Arabia was the recipient country; and if he will list the EU member states from whose governments such notifications have been received.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71795"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723863","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>​We remain deeply concerned about the human rights situation in Yemen. The Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights plays a vital role in objectively monitoring and reporting on human rights in Yemen. The UK welcomes the Government of Yemen's commitment to cooperate with the UN on the protection of human rights.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-27T09:39:51.02Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723863/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723863/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723863/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Yemen: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, if he will request an investigation by the International Humanitarian Fact-Finding Commission into allegations of grave breaches or other serious violations of the Geneva Conventions or Protocol 1 of the European Convention on Human Rights by parties to the current conflict in Yemen.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71796"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723864","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Foreign and Commonwealth Office’s Arms Export Policy Team assessed a total of 355 export licence applications in 2015-16 and a further 355 export licence applications in 2016-17. While complex or sensitive cases are referred to me or the relevant Minister, I am unable to provide accurate statistics on the number of such referrals in the time available.</p><p> </p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-27T09:46:58.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723864/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723864/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723864/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Saudi Arabia: Arms Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many export licence applications in which Saudi Arabia was the recipient country were assessed by his Department's Arms Export Policy Team in (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2016-17, and how many and what proportion of such applications were referred to (i) the relevant Minister and (ii) the Secretary of State before a recommendation was made to the Department for International Trade or its predecessor Department on whether that application should be approved.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71797"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723865","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>In 2015-16 351 export licence applications were approved by the Department for International Trade following advice from the FCO, representing a proportion of 99.1%. 354 applications out of a total of 355 were similarly approved in 2016-17, representing 99.7% of the total. Whilst complex or sensitive cases are referred to me or the relevant Minister, I am unable to provide accurate statistics on the number of such referrals in the time available.</p>","Uxbridge and South Ruislip","Boris Johnson",,"2017-04-27T09:48:43.453Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723865/answer","Biography information for Boris Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723865/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723865/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Saudi Arabia: Arms Trade","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, how many and what proportion of the export licence applications reviewed by his Department in (a) 2015-16 and (b) 2016-17 in which Saudi Arabia was the recipient country were sent to the Department for International Trade or its predecessor Department with a recommendation that those applications be approved; and how many such recommendations his Department issued following a review by (i) the relevant Minister and (ii) the Secretary of State.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71798"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723866","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The British Government has been clear in its condemnation of regime attacks against civilians in Syria, including the appalling chemical weapons attack on 4 April in Khan Sheikhoun which killed over 70 people and wounded hundreds. We supported the US action against the Shayrat airbase on 7 April. We hope it will deter further use of chemical weapons by the Syrian regime. By destroying up to 20 strike aircraft, this operation will have reduced the regime's ability to bomb civilians.</p><p>The UK also continues to support the UN mediated negotiations on a political settlement. Only a transition away from Asad can deliver sustainable peace.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2017-04-27T08:33:08.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723866/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723866/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723866/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Syria: Armed Conflict","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to help to prevent military action being taken against Syrian civilians by the Assad regime.","false","Biography information for Danny Kinahan","South Antrim","Danny Kinahan","71755"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723867","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>In October 2016, the Foreign and Commonwealth Office (FCO) made available to staff a revised Freedom of Religion or Belief (FoRB) toolkit to assist all officials working on human rights both in London and at overseas posts. The revised toolkit provides posts with ideas on how to promote freedom of religion or belief in their local context. To support implementation, we provide training to staff to increase religious literacy, including courses on religion and diplomacy. Building on the FCO's conference in October 2016, posts have been encouraged to make FoRB and countering violent extremism themes of their diplomatic and project work.</p>","Reading West","Alok Sharma",,"2017-04-27T09:04:28.383Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723867/answer","Biography information for Alok Sharma","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723867/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723867/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Diplomatic Service: Religious Freedom","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps his Department has taken to implement its revised toolkit on freedom of religion or belief by embassies overseas.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","71720"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723868","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>FCO Consular officials have requested documents from the Dutch authorities on behalf of the Liverpool Coroner. They have already passed a copy of the post mortem report to the coroner and have asked the Dutch authorities for an update on the remaining documents.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-04-27T09:50:19.603Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723868/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723868/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723868/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Michael Moran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what steps he is taking to assist the Liverpool coroner in relation to the death of Michael Moran on 1 January 2017 in the Netherlands; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","71693"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723869","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>FCO ​Consular officials have sent a list of questions from the family to the Dutch Prosecutor leading on the case and have been advised that the Dutch authorities will provide the Moran family with answers to their questions. Officials are also helping the family to arrange a meeting with the Prosecutor and a representative from the police team.</p>","Rutland and Melton","Sir Alan Duncan",,"2017-04-27T09:56:15.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723869/answer","Biography information for Sir Alan Duncan","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723869/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723869/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2017-04-24","Michael Moran","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, what representations the Government is making to the Government of the Netherlands to answer questions raised on behalf of the family of Michael Moran who died in Holland on 1 January 2017; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dame Louise Ellman","Liverpool, Riverside","Mrs Louise Ellman","71684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723870","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T09:01:44.34Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723870/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723870/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723870/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","British Pregnancy Advisory Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much has been spent from the public purse on the provision of abortions by the British Pregnancy Advisory Service in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723871","Department of Health","false","2017-04-26","<p>Decisions on the timing of introducing a remedial order to Parliament to address the incompatibility in the Human Fertility and Embryology Act 2008 will be a matter for the incoming administration.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-26T12:40:24.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723871/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723871/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723871/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Surrogate Motherhood: Lone Parents","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 8 March 2017 to Question 66737, on Surrogate mothers: lone parents, when he plans to bring forward legislative proposals to give single parents with children born through surrogacy the same rights as couples.","false","Biography information for Kirsten Oswald","East Renfrewshire","Kirsten  Oswald","71671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723872","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>Information on National Health Service expenditure on the provision of abortions by Marie Stopes UK is not collected centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Over the past five years, United Kingdom Government funding has provided central support to Marie Stopes International’s (MSI) developing country portfolio of 29 countries, and Department for International Development (DFID) specific programmes in Bangladesh, Kenya, Malawi, Pakistan and Sierra Leone. Over this period, DFID direct funding to MSI was £163.01 million.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T09:00:48.673Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723872/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723872/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723872/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Marie Stopes International","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much has been spent from the public purse on the provision of abortions by Marie Stopes UK (a) within and (b) outside the UK in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723873","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Department has not allocated any funding directly to the British Pregnancy Advisory Service. Information on contracts held by clinical commissioning groups with independent abortion providers is not collected centrally.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71645","2017-04-27T07:31:12.91Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723873/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723873/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723873/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much was spent from the public purse on the provision of abortions by independent abortion providers in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71689"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723874","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>On 1 December 2015, Wales introduced deemed consent (opt-out) for organ and tissue donation. The Department will monitor closely how these changes in legislation in Wales affect donation rates.</p><p> </p><p>Since the launch of the United Kingdom-wide Taking Organ Transplantation to 2020 Strategy in 2013, organ donation rates have increased by 7% and transplant rates by 6% mainly through a strengthening of the donation infrastructure (e.g. increased specialist nurses, improved retrieval arrangements). In 2016/17, there were 1,413 deceased donors resulting in 3,712 transplants.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T08:43:21.627Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723874/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723874/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723874/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Organs: Donors","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will consider moving to a system of presumed consent for organ donation.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","71709"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723875","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The information is not available and could only be obtained at disproportionate cost. Tables of collated numbers of reported physical assaults against National Health Service staff in England are available at:</p><p><a href="http://www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/3645.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.nhsbsa.nhs.uk/3645.aspx</a></p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-04-27T08:19:37.72Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723875/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723875/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723875/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Hospital Wards: Crimes against the Person","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many assaults have taken place on mixed-sex NHS hospital wards in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","71692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723876","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The General Practice Forward View (GPFV), published by NHS England in April 2016, listed 10 High Impact Actions that help general practitioner practices to release time for care and provide more accessible and innovative care for their patients which includes social prescribing.</p><p> </p><p>Social prescribing commonly addresses needs relating to social isolation, long term mental health issues and other personal challenges are not best addressed through medical treatment.</p><p> </p><p>The GPFV implementation programme is continuing to gather evidence about successful ways to use social prescribing. Evidence to date indicates that both clinicians and patients welcome this approach, and interest among practices is growing steadily.</p><p> </p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-04-27T07:26:40.667Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723876/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723876/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723876/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","General Practitioners: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps the Government is taking to ensure that training and development opportunities are available to staff in GP surgeries to help them to recognise loneliness and know where to refer people for help.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","71737"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723877","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him on 28 March to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=69025" target="_blank">69025</a>.</p><p> </p><p>In financial year 2012/13, the Department grant awarded to Action on Smoking and Health (ASH) (under Section 64 of the Health Services and Public Health Act 1968) was included in a sample of grants that was reviewed in an internal audit of the grant management arrangements of the Department. The audit included visits to the charities that formed part of the sample to test the information they provided to the Department and to garner their views on how the Department engaged with them. ASH was included in the work because its grant fulfilled the sample criteria.</p><p> </p><p>The internal audit was not a review of the organisation and the way that it operated, its focus was on the Department’s grant management. It found that, at the time, there were satisfactory arrangements in place in the Department. The audit report did not raise any adverse comments about ASH or include any recommendations in relation to them. It is not normal practice to place copies of Internal Audit reports in the Library.</p><p> </p><p>Minutes of annual review meetings with ASH are available on request from the Department. These documents are held for six years in line with Cabinet Office guidance.</p><p> </p><p>There is no requirement in the grant award for funding to be held in a separate account; however, the grant must be identified in annual accounts.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71727 ; 71728","2017-04-27T08:49:15.197Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723877/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723877/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723877/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Action On Smoking and Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, pursuant to the Answer of 28 March 2017 to Question 68965, on Action on Smoking and Health, what controls and checks are in place to ensure that none of the grant funds provided are used to fund lobbying activities.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","71726"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723878","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him on 28 March to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=69025" target="_blank">69025</a>.</p><p> </p><p>In financial year 2012/13, the Department grant awarded to Action on Smoking and Health (ASH) (under Section 64 of the Health Services and Public Health Act 1968) was included in a sample of grants that was reviewed in an internal audit of the grant management arrangements of the Department. The audit included visits to the charities that formed part of the sample to test the information they provided to the Department and to garner their views on how the Department engaged with them. ASH was included in the work because its grant fulfilled the sample criteria.</p><p> </p><p>The internal audit was not a review of the organisation and the way that it operated, its focus was on the Department’s grant management. It found that, at the time, there were satisfactory arrangements in place in the Department. The audit report did not raise any adverse comments about ASH or include any recommendations in relation to them. It is not normal practice to place copies of Internal Audit reports in the Library.</p><p> </p><p>Minutes of annual review meetings with ASH are available on request from the Department. These documents are held for six years in line with Cabinet Office guidance.</p><p> </p><p>There is no requirement in the grant award for funding to be held in a separate account; however, the grant must be identified in annual accounts.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71726 ; 71728","2017-04-27T08:49:15.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723878/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723878/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723878/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Action On Smoking and Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, if he will place in the Library, copies of all audits and reviews conducted by his Department in respect of the spending of grants to Action on Smoking and Health.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","71727"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723879","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave him on 28 March to Question <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-questions-answers/?page=1&amp;max=20&amp;questiontype=AllQuestions&amp;house=commons%2clords&amp;uin=69025" target="_blank">69025</a>.</p><p> </p><p>In financial year 2012/13, the Department grant awarded to Action on Smoking and Health (ASH) (under Section 64 of the Health Services and Public Health Act 1968) was included in a sample of grants that was reviewed in an internal audit of the grant management arrangements of the Department. The audit included visits to the charities that formed part of the sample to test the information they provided to the Department and to garner their views on how the Department engaged with them. ASH was included in the work because its grant fulfilled the sample criteria.</p><p> </p><p>The internal audit was not a review of the organisation and the way that it operated, its focus was on the Department’s grant management. It found that, at the time, there were satisfactory arrangements in place in the Department. The audit report did not raise any adverse comments about ASH or include any recommendations in relation to them. It is not normal practice to place copies of Internal Audit reports in the Library.</p><p> </p><p>Minutes of annual review meetings with ASH are available on request from the Department. These documents are held for six years in line with Cabinet Office guidance.</p><p> </p><p>There is no requirement in the grant award for funding to be held in a separate account; however, the grant must be identified in annual accounts.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71726 ; 71727","2017-04-27T08:49:15.337Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723879/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723879/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723879/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Action On Smoking and Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether it is a requirement that grants paid by his Department to Action on Smoking and Health (ASH) are held in a separate account by ASH to avoid those funds being spent on non-agreed activities.","false","Biography information for Mr Philip Hollobone","Kettering","Mr Philip Hollobone","71728"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723880","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The information is not available in the format requested as patient admissions to accident and emergency are not collected. Only data on attendances to accident and emergency departments is collected.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T10:13:59.237Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723880/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723880/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723880/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many admissions to accident and emergency departments of people aged under 18-years old for mental health conditions there have been in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Barbara Keeley","Worsley and Eccles South","Barbara Keeley","71821"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723881","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>We regret that we are unable to locate a copy of a letter from Tony Newton, the then Minister of State for Health, to the Rt. hon. Member for Birkenhead (Frank Field MP).</p><p> </p><p>We have published all available material before 1992 and have acknowledged that unfortunately some papers from the period were inadvertently lost or destroyed a number of years ago. This is covered in some detail in Lord Archer’s report and it is important to note that Lord Archer also made clear that his inquiry “discovered no evidence of malicious destruction of relevant records”.</p><p> </p><p>Officials have not been able to identify any of the correspondence referred to or the information it would have contained. However haemophilia centres were alert to the potential of HIV in blood products by 1983.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T09:57:27.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723881/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723881/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723881/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Blood: Contamination","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, with reference to the Answer of 11 January 1988 to the right hon. Member for Birkenhead, Official Report, column 184W, on contaminated blood products, if he will place a copy of the letter sent to that right hon. Member in the Library.","false","Biography information for Diana Johnson","Kingston upon Hull North","Diana Johnson","71814"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723883","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The information is not collected in the format requested.</p><p> </p><p>Currently it is expected that 95% of patients on Care Programme Approach (CPA) should be followed up within seven days of discharge from psychiatric inpatient care. The Quarterly Mental Health Community Teams Activity return collects data on this activity, which is published quarterly on the NHS England Statistics website:</p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/mental-health-community-teams-activity/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/mental-health-community-teams-activity/</a></p><p> </p><p>The last 12 months of available data cover Quarter 4 2015/16 to Quarter 3 2016/17 and showed that 61,612 people were followed up with seven days of discharge, 96.7% of patients on CPA. This data are available back to Quarter 1 2010/11 on the link above, during which time the 95% threshold has consistently been met nationally.</p><p> </p><p>The next report, covering Quarter 4 2016/17, will be published on 12 May.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T09:23:32.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723883/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723883/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723883/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Mental Health Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what proportion of NHS mental health patients received follow-up treatment within 48 hours after being discharged as an inpatient from a mental health facility in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Caroline Lucas","Brighton, Pavilion","Caroline Lucas","71820"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723884","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>This information is not collected centrally.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T08:57:00.467Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723884/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723884/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723884/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Eating Disorders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what effect NHS England funding changes have had on eating disorder nursing provision in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","71808"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723885","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government is investing an additional £30 million per year to improve access to effective eating disorder care in the community. The additional investment has helped to create 67 new or extended Community Eating Disorder teams across England. The ambition is to improve early access to effective care, improve outcomes and reduce relapse rates, the need for inpatient care, and length of stay when admission is required.</p><p> </p><p>For any admission, the community eating disorder team are to ensure continuity of care pre- and post- admission and maintain contact with the young person and family during admission.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T08:56:03.6Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723885/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723885/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723885/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Eating Disorders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the effect of changes to Community Support Services on readmission rates to special eating disorder units.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","71809"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723886","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>NHS England has set a new access standard, to be achieved by 2020, that 95% of patients are to be treated within four weeks of their first contact with a designated healthcare professional. For urgent cases, the standard will be one week. The very worst emergency cases should find support within 24 hours. This has been funded by £30 million each year, which is scheduled to continue until 2020.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T08:58:51.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723886/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723886/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723886/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Eating Disorders: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he has taken to ensure that children with eating disorders are treated as early as possible in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","71810"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723887","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>NHS England sets overall baseline allocations for clinical commissioning groups and does not generally determine funding for specific services. Commissioners determine their budgets locally with reference to national planning requirements like the Mental Health Investment Standard, waiting time/access targets and local needs based assessment.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T08:54:21.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723887/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723887/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723887/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Eating Disorders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what plans he has to address the difference in the level of funding for (a) adult and (b) child eating disorder service provision in England.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","71811"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723888","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) clinical guideline for the recognition and treatment of eating disorder has been updated and is scheduled to be published in May 2017.</p><p><a href="https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/indevelopment/gid-cgwave0703" target="_blank">https://www.nice.org.uk/guidance/indevelopment/gid-cgwave0703</a></p><p> </p><p>The draft clinical guideline on which NICE has consulted, emphasised that admissions should be made to an age appropriate facility, close to the young person’s home as possible and have the capacity to provide appropriate educational activities.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T08:51:01.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723888/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723888/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723888/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Eating Disorders: Children","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what assessment he has made of the risk to children with eating disorders of learned behaviours when such children are placed in general units.","false","Biography information for Melanie Onn","Great Grimsby","Melanie Onn","71812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723889","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>Data on waiting times for Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services has only been collected since 1 January 2016. The available data is published regularly as part of the Mental Health and Learning Disabilities Statistics Monthly Reports and can be accessed here:</p><p><a href="http://content.digital.nhs.uk/mhldsmonthly" target="_blank">http://content.digital.nhs.uk/mhldsmonthly</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71823 ; 71824","2017-04-27T08:41:37.647Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723889/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723889/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723889/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average waiting time was for an assessment by Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Barbara Keeley","Worsley and Eccles South","Barbara Keeley","71822"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723890","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>Data on waiting times for Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services has only been collected since 1 January 2016. The available data is published regularly as part of the Mental Health and Learning Disabilities Statistics Monthly Reports and can be accessed here:</p><p><a href="http://content.digital.nhs.uk/mhldsmonthly" target="_blank">http://content.digital.nhs.uk/mhldsmonthly</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71822 ; 71824","2017-04-27T08:41:37.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723890/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723890/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723890/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the current average waiting time is for an assessment by Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services.","false","Biography information for Barbara Keeley","Worsley and Eccles South","Barbara Keeley","71823"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723891","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>Data on waiting times for Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services has only been collected since 1 January 2016. The available data is published regularly as part of the Mental Health and Learning Disabilities Statistics Monthly Reports and can be accessed here:</p><p><a href="http://content.digital.nhs.uk/mhldsmonthly" target="_blank">http://content.digital.nhs.uk/mhldsmonthly</a></p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71822 ; 71823","2017-04-27T08:41:37.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723891/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723891/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723891/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-24","Mental Health Services: Children and Young People","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many children and young people are currently waiting for an assessment by Child and Adolescent Mental Health Services in England.","false","Biography information for Barbara Keeley","Worsley and Eccles South","Barbara Keeley","71824"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723892","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>It is for individual fire and rescue authorities to decide what training is most appropriate for their officers and where they procure it.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-26T11:02:47.07Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723892/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723892/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723892/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Fire Service College","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what support she is giving to the Fire Service College to encourage more UK fire and rescue officers to undertake training offered by that body.","false","Biography information for Sir Geoffrey Clifton-Brown","The Cotswolds","Geoffrey Clifton-Brown","71832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723893","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Modern Crime Prevention Strategy published in March 2016 sets out the Government’s strategy recognising that using modern technology effectively is critical to preventing crime. Using social media is part of this.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-27T08:38:05.19Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723893/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723893/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723893/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Police: Social Media","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if she will take steps to encourage police forces to make use of social media to (a) pass information onto communities which they serve and (b) assist in tackling crime; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","71723"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723894","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>It is crucial that police crime recorded crime statistics are accurate and fit for purpose. HMIC’s rolling programme of crime data integrity inspections will keep the spotlight on forces to improve the accuracy of their crime recording. Where those inspections highlight areas for improvement we expect forces to take them seriously and act on them. HMIC are currently conducting a crime data integrity inspection in West Midlands police with a report to be published later in the year.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-27T08:25:27.133Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723894/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723894/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723894/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Police: Bureaucracy","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to improve the effectiveness of police recording processes for crimes in (a) England and Wales and (b) the West Midlands.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","71745"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723895","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The police have increased their capability to record and respond to hate crime. The police have also improved training to staff on the identification, investigation and prosecution of hate crime. The UK has some of the most robust legislation in the world for tackling hate crime and on 26 July last year the Government published the Hate Crime Action Plan “Action Against Hate”. This outlines the work Government, law enforcement and other parties will undertake over the next four years to tackle hate crime in all its forms.</p><p>Decisions on the allocation of police resources are a matter for Chief Constables in association with local Police and Crime Commissioners.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-27T08:28:43.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723895/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723895/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723895/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Hate Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to ensure that the police have sufficient resources to deal with the reported rise in hate crimes since June 2016.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","71746"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723896","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The use of covert human intelligence sources by police forces, and the intelligence derived from this use, plays an important role in the prevention and detection of crime, and is subject to strict authorisation controls and oversight through the Office of Surveillance Commissioners, as detailed in the Covert Human Intelligence Sources Code of Practice.</p><p>Intelligence derived from covert human intelligence sources is frequently combined with intelligence and evidence from other sources to build a case for prosecutions and convictions. It is not therefore currently possible to say how many prosecutions and convictions resulted from intelligence gained from covert human intelligence sources alone, since such information will almost always form part of an overall intelligence picture. It is an operational matter for individual police forces to ensure that their use of covert human intelligence sources is effective. Law enforcement agencies must demonstrate that their use is both necessary and proportionate, and must ensure they comply with the Covert Human Intelligence Sources Code of Practice.</p><p>Available statistics and analysis on the use of covert human intelligence sources, including the number of covert human intelligence sources authorisations, are provided in the Chief Surveillance Commissioner’s annual report.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-27T08:31:47.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723896/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723896/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723896/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Informers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many (a) prosecutions and (b) convictions there have been as a direct result of information gained by police forces from covert human intelligence sources in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","71744"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723897","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Home Office has no record of any recent general representations or reports from members of the Army who have faced difficulties entering the UK at an airport.</p><p>Military personnel are checked at the UK border in line with the Border Force Operating Mandate but are exempt from immigration control if they fall under section 8 of the Immigration Act 1971 provided they can prove that they are a serving member of the British Army.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-27T08:09:58.107Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723897/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723897/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723897/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Entry Clearances: Armed Forces","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent representations she has received on reports that members of the Army are facing difficulties entering UK airports.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71769"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723898","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The 101 non-emergency contact number is led by the police. The annual crime survey for England and Wales shows that awareness of the number has increased steadily since its introduction in 2011.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-27T08:27:02.007Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723898/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723898/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723898/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","101 Calls","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of the 101 crime service; what procedures are in place to ensure that lessons are learnt from any shortcomings in that service; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","71721"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723899","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Home Office has no record of any general representations from community representatives or Fijian nationals enlisted as regulars in the British Army or with Indefinite Leave to Remain (ILR), having experienced difficulties at the UK border.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-27T08:14:03.783Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723899/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723899/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723899/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Entry Clearances: Fiji","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what recent representations she has received from community and civil society representatives on the experience of entering UK airports for Fijian citizens in the British Army with Commonwealth passports and indefinite leave to enter or remain in the UK; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71713"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723900","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>The police operational response to crime is an operational matter for chief officers. The police do have networks and tools which assist them in collaborating across police force boundaries where appropriate, which include specialist units owned jointly by a number of forces and the Regional Organised Crime Unit structure.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-27T08:37:50.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723900/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723900/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723900/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Crime","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what steps she is taking to encourage greater cross-border co-operation between different constabularies for the purposes of tackling travelling criminals in (a) rural and (b) urban areas; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Greg Knight","East Yorkshire","Sir Greg Knight","71722"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723901","Home Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>There are no current plans for a charter flight returns operation to Iraq.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-27T08:15:38.793Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723901/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723901/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723901/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-24","Deportation: Iraq","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what arrangements are in place between the Government and the Government of Iraq for removing, by charter flight to Iraq, people who have been refused asylum in the UK.","false","Biography information for Thangam Debbonaire","Bristol West","Thangam Debbonaire","71685"
