"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723937","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-27","<p>We are currently consulting with our staff at Vinovium House and Trade Unions about the proposal. The outcomes of the consultation will be reviewed and considered before making a final decision on the future of this site.</p><p> </p><p>It is necessary to delay any further announcements whilst we are in the pre-election period.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds","71764 ; 71765","2017-04-27T08:38:01.97Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723937/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723937/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723937/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-04-24","Department for Work and Pensions: Buildings","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, when he plans to publish the outcome of his Department's consultation on the proposed closure of Vinovium House.","false","Biography information for Helen Goodman","Bishop Auckland","Helen Goodman","71766"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723938","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Department is working with the Tribunals Service to establish how it can get more detailed and regular feedback on tribunal decisions. A recent initiative to use more Presenting Officers will help in this regard. The Presenting Officer will note any of the tribunal’s comments regarding the assessment, in particular anything adverse, and, where it is appropriate, feed this back to the provider.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2017-04-27T08:25:50.183Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723938/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723938/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723938/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-04-24","Personal Independence Payment: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if his Department will take steps to share personal independence payment (PIP) appeal tribunal decisions with assessment providers in order to improve the quality of initial PIP assessments.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","71691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723939","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government is determined that insurers should treat customers fairly and firms are required to do so under the current regulator, the Financial Conduct Authority.</p><p> </p><p>The Government keeps all policy under review and it will be for any new Government to set the direction of future policy on insurance premiums.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-04-27T08:04:42.437Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723939/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723939/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723939/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-24","Motor Vehicles: Insurance","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to regulate insurance premiums to protect the no-claims bonus for people who make a claim for no fault of their own.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","71682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723940","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-27","<p>Section 75 of the Consumer Credit Act 1974 sets out the potential liability of creditors for breaches by suppliers in debtor-creditor-supplier agreements, so that credit card companies must take responsibility if a supplier cannot satisfy a consumer’s purchase. To fall within section 75, there has to be an agreement to finance a transaction between a debtor and a third party supplier and there must be existing arrangements between the creditor and the supplier.</p><p> </p><p>If a credit card is used to pay through a third party intermediary service, the conditions in section 75 may not be met. This is the case where the supplier has an arrangement with the intermediary but has no arrangement or contact with the creditor. This aims to strike the right balance between consumer protections and proportionate burdens on business.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-04-27T08:05:33.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723940/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723940/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723940/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-24","Credit Cards","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what plans he has to close the loophole of third-party payment systems severing ties between a consumer and a credit card supplier for the purposes of section 75 Consumer Credit Act protection.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","71683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723941","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>The UN and EU have imposed sanctions on North Korea; these are directly applicable to the UK and prohibit the export of equipment that could be used in the North Korean nuclear programme.</p><p>All export licence applications are considered against the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria. These include in particular Criterion 1, the UK’s obligations and its commitments to enforce United Nations, European Union and Organisation for Security and Co-operation in Europe (OSCE) arms embargoes, as well as national embargoes observed by the UK and other commitments regarding the application of strategic export controls and Criterion 7, the risk that the items will be diverted within the buyer country or re-exported under undesirable conditions.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-04-27T09:47:56.48Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723941/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723941/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723941/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Nuclear Weapons: North Korea","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what steps his Department is taking to ensure that no parts made in the UK are used in the North Korean nuclear programme.","false","Biography information for Jim Shannon","Strangford","Jim Shannon","71719"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723942","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-27","<p>The evidence that present rates of decline in the extent of Arctic sea ice are not consistent with reasonably expected natural variability does not rely on computer simulations alone. Detection of the decline is based on observations. Both observations and models are used to estimate natural variability in the climate system, and attribute the most likely cause for the detected decline.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-04-27T10:41:43.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723942/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723942/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723942/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-24","Climate Change: Snow and Ice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 15 March 2017 to Question 66793, whether the climate models referred to rely on computer simulations only rather than observational evidence.","false","Biography information for Lord Lilley","Hitchin and Harpenden","Mr Peter Lilley","71752"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723943","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-27","<p>The evidence that declines of snow and ice, other than of Arctic sea ice extent, are not consistent with reasonably expected natural variability does not rely on computer simulations alone. Detection of declining snow and ice is based on observations. Both observations and models are used to estimate natural variability in the climate system, and attribute the most likely cause for the detected declines.</p><p> </p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd",,"2017-04-27T10:39:44.833Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723943/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723943/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723943/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-24","Climate Change: Snow and Ice","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, pursuant to the Answer of 29 March 2017 to Question 68956, whether the climate models referred to rely on computer simulations only rather than observational evidence.","false","Biography information for Lord Lilley","Hitchin and Harpenden","Mr Peter Lilley","71751"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723944","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2017-04-27","<p>Under terms in the supply license, energy companies must take all reasonable steps to obtain a meter reading for each customer at least once a year.</p><p>Customers may submit their own meter readings to energy companies at any time to avoid an estimated bill. If a supplier considers a customer’s reading to be reasonably accurate they must take all reasonable steps to reflect the meter reading in the next bill or statement of account. If a meter reading provided by a customer is considered not to be reasonably accurate, the supplier will ask for another reading or arrange to read the meter themselves.</p><p>The installation of smart meters, which is scheduled to be completed by 2020, should enable suppliers to provide more accurate bills, based upon actual readings transmitted by each meter.</p>","Hereford and South Herefordshire","Jesse Norman",,"2017-04-27T08:52:50.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723944/answer","Biography information for Jesse Norman","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723944/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2017-04-24","Energy: Housing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what assessment the Government has made of the accuracy of the data held by energy companies on the energy consumption patterns of households in the last 12 months.","false","Biography information for Hywel Williams","Arfon","Hywel Williams","71750"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723945","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Export Control Organisation within the Department for International Trade is the UK’s licensing authority for military and dual use exports, and the Secretary of State for International Trade is responsible for decisions to grant or refuse export licences. These decisions are always informed by assessments carried out against the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria by a number of advisory Government Departments.</p><p>I refer the hon Member for Birmingham, Hall Green to the answer I gave to the hon Member for Rutherglen and Hamilton West on 25 April 2017, UIN: 70268.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-04-27T09:46:42.353Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723945/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723945/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Arms Trade: Exports","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, which (a) Government department and (b) body is responsible for (i) assessing and (ii) authorising arms export applications.","false","Biography information for Mr Roger Godsiff","Birmingham, Hall Green","Mr Roger Godsiff","71767"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723946","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>Export Control Joint Unit full-time equivalent staffing stands at 100, of which the DIT Export Control Organisation = 78; Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office = 14; and Ministry of Defence = 8.</p><p>No staff are seconded from outside the Civil Service to the Export Control Joint Unit or Export Control Organisation. One person, a Civil Service Fast Streamer, is seconded from another Government Department to the Export Control Organisation. All other staff working within Export Control Joint Unit remain on their own departmental headcount, be it DIT/FCO/MOD.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier","71780","2017-04-27T09:43:20.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723946/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723946/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Export Control Organisation: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many full-time equivalent staff of his Department currently work in the (a) Export Control Joint Unit and (b) Export Control Organisation.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71778"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723947","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Department for International Trade promotes export opportunities to British companies through our overseas network of 174 offices across 109 countries, offering specialised support services tailored to the needs of individual opportunities, setting up trade missions and events, and providing introductions and helping address barriers to markets. Furthermore, GREAT.gov.uk helps UK business to find thousands of export opportunities in markets around the world, be on-boarded onto the world’s largest global e-commerce sites or be connected directly with international buyers.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-04-27T08:43:34.307Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723947/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723947/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Trade Promotion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what programmes his Department has put in place to use the skills and networks of UK citizens living abroad to promote UK trade.","false","Biography information for Dan Jarvis","Barnsley Central","Dan Jarvis","71794"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723948","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Export Control Joint Unit (ECJU) co-locates DIT’s Export Control Organisation (ECO) and the export licensing teams from the Ministry of Defence (MOD) and Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office (FCO). ECO is the Government’s regulatory body for military and dual use exports and the Secretary of State for International Trade is responsible for decisions to grant or refuse export licences. MOD and FCO advise the Department for International Trade on specific aspects of the Consolidated EU and National Arms Export Licensing Criteria against which each licence application is assessed.</p><p>The MOD team in ECJU also manages the Form 680 process which controls the release by industry of equipment or information with a classification of Official-Sensitive or above, including in marketing campaigns, to foreign end-users.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-04-27T09:45:53.98Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723948/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723948/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Export Control Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, if he will list the responsibilities of the Export Control Joint Unit; and what the relationship is between that unit and the Export Control Organisation.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71782"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723949","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>Export Control Joint Unit full-time equivalent staffing stands at 100, of which the DIT Export Control Organisation = 78; Foreign &amp; Commonwealth Office = 14; and Ministry of Defence = 8.</p><p>No staff are seconded from outside the Civil Service to the Export Control Joint Unit or Export Control Organisation. One person, a Civil Service Fast Streamer, is seconded from another Government Department to the Export Control Organisation. All other staff working within Export Control Joint Unit remain on their own departmental headcount, be it DIT/FCO/MOD.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier","71778","2017-04-27T09:43:20.15Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723949/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723949/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Export Control Organisation: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many people currently work within the (a) Export Control Joint Unit and (b) Export Control Organisation on secondment from (i) other Government Departments and (ii) outside the Civil Service.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71780"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723950","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Department for International Trade does not have any contracts with Deloitte.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-04-27T08:45:15.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723950/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723950/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723950/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Department for International Trade: Deloitte","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, how many contracts Deloitte has with his Department; and how much each such contract is worth.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","71701"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723951","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Department for International Trade has not awarded any tenders to Deloitte since January 2017.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-04-27T08:44:27.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723951/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723951/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723951/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Department for International Trade: Deloitte","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what tenders have been awarded to Deloitte by his Department since 1 January 2017.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","71702"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723952","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>All contractors employed to provide advice on exports and support services are provided with relevant policies and are required to comply with robust governance procedures overseen by line managers. This is underpinned by contractual obligations on contractors such as, full disclosure of interests to ensure impartiality and address potential conflict.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-04-27T08:42:35.697Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723952/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723952/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723952/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Department for International Trade: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what due diligence procedures are in place to ensure that advice on exports and support services provided by private sector contractors for his Department are independent and unbiased.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","71703"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723953","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>There are no functions of the Department for International Trade that have been entirely provided by a private company since July 2016.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-04-27T08:46:05.213Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723953/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723953/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723953/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Department for International Trade: Contracts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, which functions of his Department have been conducted by private sector providers since 1 July 2016.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","71704"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723954","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Department for International Trade operates a mixed economy of civil servants, third sector and private sector partners in the UK and in post. It elects its partners for specific services based on requirements and the organisation best placed to deliver them.</p>","Chelsea and Fulham","Greg Hands",,"2017-04-27T10:10:06.907Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723954/answer","Biography information for Greg Hands","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723954/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Trade Promotion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what proportion of international trade and exporting advice services provided by his Department has been subcontracted to private businesses.","false","Biography information for Barry Gardiner","Brent North","Barry Gardiner","71700"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723955","Department for International Trade","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Export Control Joint Unit (ECJU) is funded by the contributing departments through their own budgets. The Department for International Trade provides the office space, with each department funding its own staff and IT systems. As such there is no specific operating budget.</p><p>The annual operating budget for DIT’s Export Control Organisation in 2016/17 was £3.2m.</p>","Wyre Forest","Mark Garnier",,"2017-04-27T09:45:04.463Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723955/answer","Biography information for Mark Garnier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723955/answer",,,,,"202","International Trade","International Trade","2017-04-24","Export Control Organisation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Trade, what the total operating budget of the (a) Export Control Joint Unit and (b) Export Control Organisation was in the most recent year for which figures are available.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71800"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723956","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>The UK Government is committed to involving the Overseas Territories as we prepare to exit the EU, and ensuring their interests are properly taken into account.</p><p>UK Ministers and leaders of the Overseas Territories have committed to taking forward future engagement through the creation of the UK – Overseas Territories Joint Ministerial Council (JMC) on European Negotiations.</p><p>The JMC met for the first time on 6-7 February 2017, chaired jointly by myself, Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State at the Department for Exiting the European Union, and Foreign Office Minister Baroness Anelay, and discussed a range of issues of interest to the Overseas Territories. <br><br></p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-27T09:07:47.377Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723956/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723956/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723956/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-24","British Overseas Territories","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what discussions his Department has had with the Overseas Territories on the implications for those territories of the UK leaving the EU.","false","Biography information for Neil Parish","Tiverton and Honiton","Neil Parish","71789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723957","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government has been conducting a programme of rigorous and extensive analytical work that will help define our partnership with the EU, and inform our understanding of how EU exit will affect the UK’s domestic policies and frameworks. Parliament has voted repeatedly not to publish detail which could undermine UK's position in our negotiations with the EU and the Government will repeat repeat that decision.</p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-27T09:19:55.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723957/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723957/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723957/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-24","European Union (Notification of Withdrawal) Bill","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, whether the Government plans to publish a regulatory impact assessment for the European Union (Notification of Withdrawal) Bill.","false","Biography information for Alex Salmond","Gordon","Alex Salmond","71825"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723958","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-27","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-04-27T09:47:51.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723958/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723958/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-04-24","Facebook","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, how much the Government spent from the public purse on targeted Facebook advertising to promote the planforbritain.gov.uk website.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","71680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723960","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government has been clear that we should always put citizens first. This was reflected in the Prime Minister’s letter to the President of the European Council confirming the Government’s decision to invoke Article 50. We want to strike an early agreement about the rights of EU nationals in the UK and UK nationals in the EU and made clear that we would have been happy to do so in advance of negotiations. We will look to prioritise this issue as soon as negotiations begin.<br><br></p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-27T09:16:07.42Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723960/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723960/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723960/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-24","Immigration: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, if he will make it his priority to secure residency rights for EU nationals living in the UK with British children or other dependents.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71772"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723090","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>It has not proved possible to respond to the hon. Member in the time available before Prorogation.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-04-26T16:24:14.257Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723090/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723090/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723090/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-04-21","Chemical Weapons: Syria","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if he will publish the Joint Intelligence Committee's findings on the chemical weapons attack of 4 April 2017 in Khan Sheikhoun.","false","Biography information for Emily Thornberry","Islington South and Finsbury","Emily Thornberry","71565"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723091","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>The franchise for the Parliamentary election remains unchanged as set out in the Representation of the People Acts 1983 and 1985.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-04-26T13:08:08.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723091/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723091/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-04-21","Voting Rights: EU Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, whether the Government plans to bring forward legislative proposals to extend the franchise to EU nationals for the 8 June 2017 UK general election.","false","Biography information for Margaret Ferrier","Rutherglen and Hamilton West","Margaret Ferrier","71556"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723092","Department for Transport","false","2017-04-26","<p>The last triennial review (now known as the tailored review) for HS2 Ltd was conducted in 2011. The report into this review is provided in the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/3654/hs2-ltd-triennial-review-2011.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/3654/hs2-ltd-triennial-review-2011.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>The Department is planning to undertake a tailored review for HS2 Ltd in 2017/18.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-04-26T14:59:12.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723092/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723092/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-04-21","High Speed Two","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when the last tailored or triennial review of HS2 Ltd was; and when the next such review is due.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","71562"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723093","Cabinet Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>Since the 2015 general election, Parliament has debated lowering the voting age to 16 a number of times and has repeatedly voted against it.</p>","Kingswood","Chris Skidmore",,"2017-04-26T11:08:18.323Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723093/answer","Biography information for Chris Skidmore","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723093/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-04-21","Voting Rights","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, if his Department will bring forward legislative proposals to allow people over the age of 16 to vote in elections.","false","Biography information for Alex Salmond","Gordon","Alex Salmond","71585"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723094","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-26","<p>HM Revenue and Customs (HMRC) do not comment on individual cases. Anyone who feels they have been underpaid National Minimum Wage or National Living Wage should contact the Acas helpline on 0300 123 1100. HMRC review all complaints that are referred to them.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-04-26T15:14:42.823Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723094/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723094/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723094/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-21","Minimum Wage: Care Homes","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, which social care providers have been identified by HM Revenue and Customs as non-compliant with national minimum wage legislation; how much is owed in arrears by each such provider; to how many staff such arrears are owed; and what value of fines have been levied on care providers to date.","false","Biography information for Barbara Keeley","Worsley and Eccles South","Barbara Keeley","71600"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723095","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-26","<p>HM Revenue and Customs expects to publish the post-implementation review of real time information later this year.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-04-26T15:11:03.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723095/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723095/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-21","Taxation: Electronic Government","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 24 November 2016 to Question 53970, when HM Revenue and Customs plans to publish the post-implementation review of Real Time Information.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","71628"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723096","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-26","<p>The government welcomes investment from investors all over the world, including Sovereign Wealth Funds.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-04-26T14:45:24.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723096/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723096/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-21","Sovereign Wealth Funds","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how he plans to maximise the effect of investment of sovereign wealth funds in the UK in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71618"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723097","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-26","<p>The government welcomes investment from investors all over the world, including Sovereign Wealth Funds.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-04-26T14:44:45.63Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723097/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723097/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723097/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-21","Sovereign Wealth Funds","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how he plans to maximise investment in the UK by sovereign wealth funds in each of the next five years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71619"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723098","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-26","<p>The National Infrastructure Delivery Plan set out the government’s plan for attracting inward investment through infrastructure development.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-04-26T14:43:11.23Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723098/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723098/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723098/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-21","Sovereign Wealth Funds","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, whether the Government has a strategy for (a) current and (b) future collaboration with sovereign wealth funds; and if he will publish that strategy.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71620"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723099","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-26","<p>There are 349 public halls and 1,158 nightclubs and discotheques with a rateable value less than £100,000 in England, as identified by the categorisation used for compiling the 2017 Rating Lists.</p><p> </p><p>There is no classification specifically for music venues so it is not possible to reliably estimate a number for that category.</p>","Battersea","Jane Ellison",,"2017-04-26T15:09:29.727Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723099/answer","Biography information for Jane Ellison","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723099/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723099/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-21","Non-domestic Rates","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many (a) music venues, (b) nightclubs and discoteques and (c) public halls in England have a rateable value of less than £100,000.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","71630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723100","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-26","<p>The UK is open to investment from all sources. There are well-developed markets for professional and financial advice that support this. There are no specific protections relating to sovereign wealth funds.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-04-26T14:42:24.2Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723100/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723100/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723100/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-21","Sovereign Wealth Funds","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what additional financial and legal protections are in place for UK firms and agencies which (a) collaborate with and (b) take investment from sovereign wealth funds.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71621"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723101","Department for Exiting the European Union","false","2017-04-27","<p>The future of our relationship with the European Medicines Agency, and any potential effects on the wider health and life sciences sector, is subject to the outcome of the withdrawal negotiations. We have been clear that we will secure a deal that works for the entire United Kingdom. <br><br></p><p> </p>","Worcester","Mr Robin Walker",,"2017-04-27T09:19:13.687Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723101/answer","Biography information for Mr Robin Walker","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723101/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723101/answer",,,,,"203","Exiting the European Union","Exiting the European Union","2017-04-21","European Banking Authority: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Exiting the European Union, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on the Scottish health and life science sectors and wider economy of the European Medicines Agency headquarters leaving the UK.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71579"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723102","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-26","<p>The future of our relationship with the European Banking Authority (EBA), and any potential effects on the wider banking sector relating to the location of EBA staff, is subject to the outcome of the withdrawal negotiations.</p>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-04-26T14:40:02.87Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723102/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723102/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-21","European Banking Authority: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on the Scottish financial industry and wider economy of the European Banking Agency headquarters leaving the UK.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71580"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723103","HM Treasury","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Government has been in contact with Diageo and understands the company has begun a consultation with staff about proposed operational changes. The Government understands this will be a worrying time for Diageo employees and their families.</p><p> </p><p>Job Centre Plus stands ready to assist in the event of redundancies being confirmed, and the Government continues to support the Scottish economy and key sectors such as the food and drinks industry.</p>","South West Hertfordshire","Mr David Gauke",,"2017-04-26T16:17:24.77Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723103/answer","Biography information for Mr David Gauke","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723103/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723103/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-04-21","Diageo: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of Diageo's plans for 100 job losses on the Scottish economy.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71542"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723104","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-26","<p>Between 2011-12 and 2015-16, total net housing additions in West Sussex were 15,280, of which 3,470 were accounted for by Mid Sussex. The planning system offers a number of tools to help ensure development of new homes contribute to meeting infrastructure need, including the community infrastructure levy and planning obligations where necessary to make development acceptable. Although my Department does not monitor the full range of infrastructure spending in local areas, government publishes detailed annual data of each local authority’s capital expenditure.</p><p>This is available at:<a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-capital-expenditure-receipts-and-financing" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/local-authority-capital-expenditure-receipts-and-financing</a>.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-26T14:04:48.873Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723104/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723104/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723104/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-21","Infrastructure: Sussex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment he has made of the extent to which extra infrastructure spending in (a) Mid Sussex and (b) West Sussex has been in line with new house building; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","71571"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723105","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Department will assess the effectiveness of the current licensing scheme adopted by the London Borough of Newham in delivering its objectives under Part 3 of the Housing Act 2004 if and when an application is made to the Secretary of State by the borough for confirmation of any further licensing designation under the provisions of the Act.</p><p> </p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-26T10:52:54.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723105/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723105/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723105/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-21","Landlords: Newham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what assessment his Department has made of the effectiveness of the Landlord Licensing Scheme introduced by the London Borough of Newham on improving the (a) detection of housing benefit fraud and (b) reclamation of funds fraudulently obtained.","false","Biography information for Lyn Brown","West Ham","Lyn Brown","71587"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723106","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2017-04-26","<p>We have strengthened Neighbourhood Planning through the Neighbourhood Planning (General) and Development Management Procedure (Amendment) Regulations 2016 that implement powers in the Housing and Planning Act 2016 and proposed measures in the Neighbourhood Planning Bill. In addition, my recent Neighbourhood Planning written ministerial statement of 12 December 2016 further strengthened Neighbourhood Planning by making it clear that where communities have planned for housing in their area through a recent neighbourhood plan, that those relevant policies should not be deemed to be “out-of-date” unless there is a significant lack of land supply for housing in the wider local authority area.</p><p>The Government has made available £22.5 million to support Neighbourhood Planning through the 2015-18 support programme. The Housing White Paper 2017 set out our intention to make further funding available to neighbourhood planning groups from 2018-2020.</p>","Croydon Central","Gavin Barwell",,"2017-04-26T14:55:12.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723106/answer","Biography information for Lord Barwell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723106/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723106/answer",,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2017-04-21","Neighbourhood Development Plans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps he is taking to strengthen Neighbourhood Plans; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","71591"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723107","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>Sport England National Lottery and Exchequer grant investment in grassroots sport, broken down by constituency, is publicly available on Sport England’s website: www.sportengland.org/funding/investments-weve-made.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2017-04-26T09:26:33.28Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723107/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723107/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723107/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-21","Sport England: Grants","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, how much (a) total and (b) per capita funding is provided by Sport England in each (i) region and (ii) county.","false","Biography information for Tim Farron","Westmorland and Lonsdale","Tim Farron","71629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723108","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2017-04-26","<p>I refer the Hon. Gentleman to the written statement made by the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport on 24 April 2017, Official Report Vol 624, Col 56WS</p><a href="https://hansard.parliament.uk/commons/2017-04-24/debates/1704249000010/SkyFoxMerger" target="_blank">https://hansard.parliament.uk/commons/2017-04-24/debates/1704249000010/SkyFoxMerger</a>","West Suffolk","Matt Hancock","71572","2017-04-26T09:08:17.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723108/answer","Biography information for Matt Hancock","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723108/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723108/answer",,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2017-04-21","Sky: 21st Century Fox","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what the effect of the General election 2017 and purdah period is on the 40-day deadline by which Ofcom is required to assess the bid by 21st Century Fox to take over Sky.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","71533"
