"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723175","Department of Health","false","2017-04-26","<p>Clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) are responsible for the contracting of independent sector places to perform termination of pregnancy. Information on contracts held by CCGs is not collected centrally.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-26T12:37:02.623Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723175/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723175/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723175/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether public funds given to private abortion providers is ring-fenced for services only; and what steps his Department has taken to ensure that surplus made from such services is not used for lobbying to change the law on abortion.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71561"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723176","Department of Health","false","2017-04-26","<p>Clinical commissioning groups (CCGs) are responsible for commissioning local health services and ensuring the needs of the local health population are met. NHS England is responsible for oversight of the commissioning system. National Institute for Health and Care Excellence (NICE) guidelines are evidence based best practice for clinicians but are not mandatory.</p><p> </p><p>I have written to NHS England specifically asking that it re-emphasise to all those involved in commissioning fertility services that they should have regard to the NICE fertility guidelines. In the light of the response to that letter, the Department will consider what further action may be appropriate.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England and professional and stakeholder groups including the Human Fertilisation and Embryology Authority, are working together to develop commissioning guidance. This guidance aims to improve the quality of commissioning and further encourage the implementation of the NICE fertility guidelines. NHS England has agreed to disseminate and promote the commissioning guidance to all CCGs in England.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71611","2017-04-26T09:42:24.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723176/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723176/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723176/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","Fertility: Medical Treatments","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what steps he is taking to maintain or increase levels of investment in NHS fertility services other than by the development of benchmark pricing.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","71544"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723177","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>Centrally held data, available from 2014/15 onwards, indicates that no specific central funding has been provided by the Department for projects related to the rebuilding of St Helier Hospital. There are currently no formal applications with either the Department or NHS Improvement seeking funding for this purpose in future years.</p>","Ludlow","Mr Philip Dunne",,"2017-04-27T08:24:49.163Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723177/answer","Biography information for Mr Philip Dunne","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723177/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723177/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","St Helier Hospital","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what funding has been allocated in the NHS budget to enable the Epsom and St Helier NHS Trust to rebuild St Helier Hospital.","false","Biography information for Tom Brake","Carshalton and Wallington","Tom Brake","71532"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723178","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Department and Public Health England (PHE) have provided funding to a number of sexual health charities, including Brook and the Family Planning Association in the past five years through the Innovation, Excellence and Strategic Development fund. These contracts are for national HIV prevention, specialist sexual health information services and other nationally funded work. Total allocations are:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2012/13:</p></td><td><p>£3,215,362</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14:</p></td><td><p>£3,021,434</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15:</p></td><td><p>£3,119,318</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16:</p></td><td><p>£1,672,660</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016/17:</p></td><td><p>£1,758,120</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>In addition, PHE has run an HIV Prevention Innovation Fund for local voluntary sector organisations in 2015 (up to £500,000) and 2016 (up to £600,000) and are running another call in 2017.</p><p> </p><p>Details of the 2015 and 2016 funds are publically available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://publichealthmatters.blog.gov.uk/2016/12/01/health-matters-a-look-at-the-hiv-prevention-innovation-fund/" target="_blank">https://publichealthmatters.blog.gov.uk/2016/12/01/health-matters-a-look-at-the-hiv-prevention-innovation-fund/</a></p><p> </p><p>with details on specific call available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/launch-of-innovative-hiv-prevention-fund" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/launch-of-innovative-hiv-prevention-fund</a></p><p> </p><p>and:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/news/new-funding-for-local-hiv-prevention" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/new-funding-for-local-hiv-prevention</a></p><p> </p><p>Information on contracts local authorities hold with sexual health charities is not collected centrally.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71643 ; 71644","2017-04-27T08:29:05.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723178/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723178/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723178/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","Health Education: Sex","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much his Department has allocated to sexual health charities (a) directly and (b) through local authorities in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71530"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723179","Department of Health","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Department does not directly fund services that provide advice on unplanned or crisis pregnancies. The Government’s Framework for Sexual Health Improvement in England (2013) sets out that women considering an abortion should be referred or signposted to services which provide impartial, accurate information and, if required, counselling on the full range of options available to women.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71552","2017-04-26T15:03:20.203Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723179/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723179/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723179/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","Abortion: Clinics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what alternatives to abortion are offered by clinics which provide NHS-funded abortions when providing abortions which are so funded.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71538"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723180","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Government published a consultation on 22 August 2016 on the scope of performance assessment of providers regulated by the Care Quality Commission. This included proposals to apply performance ratings to additional provider sectors, including termination of pregnancy services. The document is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/547103/Scope_of_CQC_ratings_Con_Doc_A.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/547103/Scope_of_CQC_ratings_Con_Doc_A.pdf</a></p><p> </p><p>It is the intention of the present Government to bring forward regulations to extend performance ratings to this sector.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-27T08:27:07.737Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723180/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723180/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723180/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","Abortion: Clinics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, whether his Department plans to give ratings to private abortion clinics in the same way in which the Care Quality Commission gives such ratings to NHS clinics.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71539"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723181","Department of Health","false","2017-04-27","<p>The Department has not allocated any funding directly to the British Pregnancy Advisory Service. Information on contracts held by clinical commissioning groups with independent abortion providers is not collected centrally.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood","71689","2017-04-27T07:31:12.863Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723181/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723181/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723181/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","British Pregnancy Advisory Service","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much his Department has allocated to the British Pregnancy Advisory Service (a) directly and (b) indirectly through contracts in each of the last five years; and what those funds were spent.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71645"
