"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723184","Department of Health","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Care Quality Commission (CQC) is the independent regulator of health and adult social care in England. All providers of regulated activities, including National Health Service and independent providers, have to register with the CQC and follow a set of fundamental standards of safety and quality below which care should never fall. The fundamental standards describe the basic requirements that providers should always meet, and outline the outcomes that services users should always expect.</p><p> </p><p>The CQC inspects providers against the fundamental standards and publishes the results on its website to help people choose care.</p><p> </p><p>The CQC has provided the following information:</p><p> </p><p>The attached table shows showing the number of care home locations<sup>1</sup> found in breach of the Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) (HSCA RA) Regulations 2014 Regulation 10 or Regulation 12 in inspections published between 1 April 2015<sup>2</sup> and 31 March 2017 and total number of care homes with an inspection published between 1 April 2015<sup>2</sup> and 31 March 2017.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","71650","2017-04-26T14:52:12.773Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723184/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723184/answer","PQ71649 attached document.docx","PQ71649 attached document.docx","PQ71649 attached table","PQ71649 attached table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723184/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","Care Homes: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many care homes inspected by the Care Quality Commission did not meet the requirements set out in Regulation 10 of the Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) Regulations 2014 in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Barbara Keeley","Worsley and Eccles South","Barbara Keeley","71649"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723185","Department of Health","false","2017-04-26","<p>The Care Quality Commission (CQC) is the independent regulator of health and adult social care in England. All providers of regulated activities, including National Health Service and independent providers, have to register with the CQC and follow a set of fundamental standards of safety and quality below which care should never fall. The fundamental standards describe the basic requirements that providers should always meet, and outline the outcomes that services users should always expect.</p><p> </p><p>The CQC inspects providers against the fundamental standards and publishes the results on its website to help people choose care.</p><p> </p><p>The CQC has provided the following information:</p><p> </p><p>The attached table shows showing the number of care home locations<sup>1</sup> found in breach of the Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) (HSCA RA) Regulations 2014 Regulation 10 or Regulation 12 in inspections published between 1 April 2015<sup>2</sup> and 31 March 2017 and total number of care homes with an inspection published between 1 April 2015<sup>2</sup> and 31 March 2017.</p>","Warrington South","David Mowat","71649","2017-04-26T14:52:12.897Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723185/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723185/answer","PQ71649 attached document.docx","PQ71649 attached document.docx","PQ71649 attached table","PQ71649 attached table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723185/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","Care Homes: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many care homes inspected by the Care Quality Commission did not meet the requirements set out in Regulation 12 of the Health and Social Care Act 2008 (Regulated Activities) Regulations 2014 in each of the last three years.","false","Biography information for Barbara Keeley","Worsley and Eccles South","Barbara Keeley","71650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723186","Department of Health","false","2017-04-26","<p>Information about expenditure on abortions is not collected centrally.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-04-26T12:38:04.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723186/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723186/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723186/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-04-21","Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how much his Department has spent on providing abortions in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71647"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723187","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>Special Grant funding of up to £1.4million has been awarded to the PCC for South Wales Police to support their policing operation around the Champions League Finals in Cardiff.</p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2017-04-26T08:39:54.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723187/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723187/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723187/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-21","South Wales Police","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether additional resources are being made available to South Wales Police to assist with the costs of policing the Men's and Women's UEFA Champions League Finals in Cardiff in June 2017.","false","Biography information for Jo Stevens","Cardiff Central","Jo Stevens","71605"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723188","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>The cross-system Detention Gatekeeper has now been introduced to scrutinise all proposed detentions independently of an arresting team. Individuals can now only enter immigration detention with the authority of the Detention Gatekeeper, who will ensure that there is no evidence of vulnerability which would be exacerbated by detention, that return will occur within a reasonable timeframe and check that any proposed detention is lawful.</p><p> </p><p>Separately, Case Progression Panels have been introduced to review all cases within immigration detention by a peer-led panel. These panels focus on ensuring that there is progression toward return for all individuals detained, and that detention remains lawful.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-26T09:54:28.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723188/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723188/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723188/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-21","Immigrants: Detainees","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, whether procedures have changed as a result of recent successful prosecutions for unlawful immigration detention.","false","Biography information for Dr Sarah Wollaston","Totnes","Dr Sarah Wollaston","71612"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723189","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>(a) Immigration Enforcement (IE) and (b) UK Visas &amp; Immigration (UKVI) were formed in April 2013. From June 2014, IE and UKVI figures are published quarterly on gov.uk - <a href="https://www.gov.uk/search?q=Border+and+immigration+cross+cutting+data" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/search?q=Border+and+immigration+cross+cutting+data</a></p><p> </p><p>(c) Border Force figures for 2012/13 to 2015/16 were given in response to the answer given to the Hon. Member for Westmorland and Lonsdale, UIN 60627.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-26T08:40:24.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723189/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723189/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723189/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-21","Home Office: Staff","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many full-time equivalent staff there have been in (a) Immigration Enforcement, (b) UK Visa and Immigration and (c) Border Force in each year since 2012.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","71636"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723190","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>The number of people who have been resettled under the Syrian Vulnerable Persons Resettlement scheme is published in the quarterly Home Office immigration statistics. Since the scheme began in January 2014 a total of 5,706 people have been resettled in the UK to the end of December 2016. The figure includes those Syrians resettled with a community sponsor during this period.</p><p> </p><p>We have seen considerable interest in the scheme from across the UK and are working with a number of groups as they develop their plans. Supporting a vulnerable resettled family is a significant responsibility and it is only right that we carefully assess every sponsoring organisation. We will, therefore, not be providing a running commentary on numbers that have been resettled with a community sponsor or how many community groups have signed up to the scheme.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-26T09:57:49.447Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723190/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723190/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723190/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-21","Refugees: Sponsorship","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many community groups have signed up to the Community Sponsorship scheme since it was launched.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","71638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723191","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>We are making progress to meet our commitments, made at the World Humanitarian Summit, on localisation. Globally DFID is the largest donor to the Country Based Pooled Funds and continues to invest in civil society consortia that support localisation. This includes through the centrally managed Disasters and Emergencies Preparedness Programme (DEPP) which invests in the longer-term capacity development of national and local NGOs in contexts of high humanitarian risk. In East Africa, DEPP supports 15 projects in Kenya, Ethiopia and South Sudan. Where we are required to deliver rapidly and across multiple contexts, such as in the east Africa food crisis, international assistance remains necessary to deliver at scale.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-04-26T15:37:51.193Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723191/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723191/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723191/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-21","East Africa: Famine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps her Department is taking to meet commitments made at the World Humanitarian Summit in May 2016 on providing funding for local and national actors to respond to the East Africa food crisis.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","71662"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723192","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>DFID conducts Annual Reviews of the Disasters and Emergencies Preparedness Programme (DEPP). The Annual Reviews are publically available through <a href="https://devtracker.dfid.gov.uk/projects/GB-1-203044" target="_blank">https://devtracker.dfid.gov.uk/projects/GB-1-203044</a> and give an assessment of the effectiveness of the programme.</p><p>The DEPP’s 14 core projects are due to end in March 2018. Decisions on whether and/or how to renew the programme will be made before March 2018.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2017-04-26T15:35:02.09Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723192/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723192/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723192/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-21","Disaster Relief","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what assessment she has made of the effectiveness of the Disaster and Emergencies Preparedness Programme funded by UK Aid; and when she plans to decide whether that programme should be renewed.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","71663"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723193","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>DFID’s position on what we can and cannot support is set out in our policy paper on safe and unsafe abortion available online at <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/safe-and-unsafe-abortion-uks-policy-position-on-safe-and-unsafe-abortion-in-developing-countries" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/safe-and-unsafe-abortion-uks-policy-position-on-safe-and-unsafe-abortion-in-developing-countries</a></p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-04-26T15:38:18.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723193/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723193/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723193/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-21","Developing Countries: Abortion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, whether any of her Department's funding for abortion services in developing countries has been allocated to countries where abortion is illegal.","false","Biography information for Fiona Bruce","Congleton","Fiona Bruce","71665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723194","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>DFID has provided £83.5 million to the Ethiopia Humanitarian Fund (EHF) over the last five years from the total DFID bilateral funding listed in the table below. In 2015/16, the EHF provided £29 million of life-saving support to 4.3 million people during Ethiopia’s worst drought in 30 years. Approximately £4.4 million of this funding was delivered by local and national NGOs.</p><p>In addition to our bilateral funding, targeted support is being provided through DFID’s centrally managed Disasters Emergency Preparedness Programme to deliver 5 projects supporting national and local NGOs in Ethiopia to engage more effectively in humanitarian preparedness and response.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>DFID bilateral programme outturn (in £s)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>336,426,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>336,355,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>284,360,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>261,460,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Figures for financial year 2016/17 will be published in the DFID Annual Report and accounts due for publication in Summer 2017.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-04-26T15:41:01.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723194/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723194/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723194/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-21","Ethiopia: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many Ethiopian local and national non-governmental organisations received humanitarian aid from her Department; and what proportion of her Department's overall aid for Ethiopia this represented in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","71660"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723195","Department for International Development","false","2017-04-26","<p>From the total DFID bilateral funding listed below, the department has provided £1,960,000 over the past five years to the Kenya Red Cross Society through the British Red Cross Society. The funds have been used to strengthen the Kenya Red Cross Society’s preparedness and response systems, assisting many households affected by disasters, such as the current drought, across Kenya.</p><p>In addition to our bilateral funding, targeted support is being provided through DFID’s centrally managed Disasters Emergency Preparedness Programme to deliver 7 projects supporting national and local NGOs in Kenya to engage more effectively in humanitarian preparedness and response.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Financial Year</p></td><td><p>DFID bilateral programme outturn (in £s)</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015/16</p></td><td><p>137,482,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>95,921,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>136,200,000</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>91,800,000</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Figures for financial year 2016/17 will be published in the DFID Annual Report and accounts due for publication in Summer 2017.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2017-04-26T15:39:27.113Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723195/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723195/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723195/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2017-04-21","Kenya: Humanitarian Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, how many Kenyan local and national non-governmental organisations received humanitarian aid from her Department; and what proportion of her Department's overall aid for Kenya this represented in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Patrick Grady","Glasgow North","Patrick Grady","71661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723196","Home Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>The information requested is recorded on electronic and paper files. Therefore the specific data requested is not aggregated in national reporting systems. To provide the information would require a disproportionately expensive manual case search.</p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2017-04-26T10:00:45.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723196/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723196/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723196/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2017-04-21","Offenders: Deportation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, how many foreign offenders have been deported twice or more in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Karl Turner","Kingston upon Hull East","Karl Turner","71637"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723198","Scotland Office","false","2017-04-26","<p>Scotland Office officials have been working closely with colleagues across the UK Government, as well as discussing directly with Diageo, to find a constructive way forward for the Leven and Shieldhall sites.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2017-04-26T10:02:48.973Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723198/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723198/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/723198/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2017-04-21","Diageo: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions his Department has had with other Departments about Diageo's decision to terminate 100 jobs in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Stephen Gethins","North East Fife","Stephen Gethins","71540"
