"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722939","Attorney General","false","2017-04-27","<p>Two people were prosecuted in February 2015 for an offence under section 1 of the Female Genital Mutilation Act 2003 and an offence of intentionally encouraging or assisting the commission of an offence, contrary to section 44(1) of the Serious Crime Act 2007. There have been no other prosecutions and no convictions for offences under the Act or other associated offences.</p>","Kenilworth and Southam","Jeremy Wright",,"2017-04-27T08:54:13.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722939/answer","Biography information for Jeremy Wright","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722939/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/722939/answer",,,,,"88","Attorney General","Attorney General","2017-04-20","Female Genital Mutilation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Attorney General, how many people have been (a) prosecuted for and (b) convicted of female genital mutilation or associated offences.","false","Biography information for Mr Jonathan Lord","Woking","Mr Jonathan Lord","71474"
